title: pepperoni surprise
directions: Mix pepperoni, pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese together in large bowl.
Spread biscuits out to 3-inch diameter on greased pan. Add one round tablespoonful of mix to center.
Pinch biscuits together and flip over on pan.
Sprinkle tops of biscuits with milk.
Then sprinkle Parmesan cheese over them.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 20.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter and beat in eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix and then add cheese and spinach.
(Squeeze as much water out of thawed spinach as you can.) Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350° or until a little brown and solid.
Cool for 45 minutes and cut into 50 squares. After cutting, you may freeze on cookie sheet and transfer to bag. To reheat, bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Rub meat with salt to taste and pepper.
Place in Tupperware. Cover with spices and vegetables blended with vinegar in a blender.
Heat vinegar with water to boil and pour over meat.
Let cool.
Cover and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Turn.
Dry with paper towel.
Strain marinade over after browning in butter. Cover and simmer 2 hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: Arrange cake on bottom of pan or bowl.
Strain oranges; place 1/2 on bottom of cake and pour sherry over.
Prepare jello, let cool and pour sherry over cake and oranges.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Make pudding and pour over cake and jello mixture for 1 hour.
Whip cream and spread over top of pudding.
Sprinkle coconut over top and decorate with orange slices.
Serve same day. Serves 8 to 10.

title: nutted wild rice
directions: Put rice in a strainer and run under cold water; rinse thoroughly.
Place rice in a medium-size saucepan.
Add stock or water and bring to a rapid boil.
Adjust heat to a gentle simmer and cook uncovered for 45 minutes.
After 30 minutes, check for doneness; rice should not be too soft.
Place a thin towel inside a colander and turn rice into the colander and drain.
Transfer drained rice to a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients to rice and toss gently.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Let mixture stand for 2 hours to allow flavors to develop.
Serve at room temperature. Makes 6 portions.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix together All-Bran, milk, bananas, egg and oil.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Leave some lumps.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Makes 12.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil, then cool. Pour over beans.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine garlic and butter in 1-quart casserole.
Cook at High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add parsley and salt.
Stir in shrimp, coating each with butter sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at Medium 4 1/2 to 6 minutes.
Stir once.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes. Sprinkle lemon juice over shrimp before serving.

title: carrot-potato scallops
directions: Pare carrots and cut into 1/8-inch diagonal slices. Pare potatoes and cut into 1/8-inch crosswise slices. Place in alternating layers in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish or casserole. Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour and salt; stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Add chives and caraway seed. Pour over carrots and potatoes in casserole.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer until carrots and potatoes are tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tomato and mozzarella salad
directions: Cut cheese slices in half diagonally.
On medium sized serving plate, alternate tomato and cheese slices.
Drizzle dressing over salad.
Sprinkle with basil.

title: chili macaroni
directions: Cook hamburger until almost browned; drain grease.
Add onion, celery, garlic and carrots.
Season with salt and pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
Drain any remaining grease.
Add tomatoes, chiles and beans; simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Mix in macaroni. Add chili powder according to your family's taste.

title: melty cheese
directions: Blend all until smooth.
Cook in heavy saucepan until thick, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Great as dip for chips or as sauce.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until everything is moistened and soft.
When everything is moist and blended, put dressing in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Dressing should be lightly browned.

title: classy casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with rice and soup mix.
Blend mushroom soup and water; pour over rice.
Spread onions on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oreole cookie cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk and chill.
Layer crumbled cookies in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, butter and Cool Whip with chilled pudding.
Pour over crushed cookies.
Garnish with some crushed Oreo's.

title: cheese zucchini salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and add seasonings to taste.
Serve with oil and vinegar or other dressing.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water with marshmallows until dissolved.
Add Mountain Dew and drained pineapple.
Chill until set.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of gelatin which has set.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook shrimp and sausage in oil and butter in a large saucepan over low flame for 5 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except green onions and parsley; heat to boiling.
Reduce flame and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Five minutes before the Jambalaya is done, add green onions and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti mexicano
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in garlic, chili powder, oregano, cumin, red kidney beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and red pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti and garnish with cheese and lettuce on top.
Serves 4.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening with an electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrap sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at medium speed, until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered with a damp cloth until ready to use.
For best results keep icing bowl in refrigerator when not using.
This icing can be stored two weeks by refrigerating in an air-tight container.
Rewhip before using.
Yield: three cups.
Add two additional Tbsp of milk per recipe to thin for icing cake.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart onto aluminum foil-lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool completely before removing.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt shortening in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar; mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and chips; mix.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry gelatin mold
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: orange yogurt salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and yogurt.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: honey tea
directions: Mix together and put into a 1 gallon jug.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise but not all the way through.
Fill opening with mashed potatoes.
Place under broiler.
Cook until potatoes begin to brown.
Place a slice of cheese on top of each hot dog and broil until cheese has melted.

title: mandarin float
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; add boiling water and sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Add milk and extract.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until set.
Cut into cubes.
Put in serving dish and top with oranges.

title: german potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook in boiling water with their skins on until tender when tested with a fork.
Drain, peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Season with salt, pepper and chopped onion and set at back of the stove while making the dressing.

title: low calorie quiche
directions: Place mushrooms, cheese and onion flakes on the bottom of small pie pan or casserole.
Place remaining ingredients in blender; blend well and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shrimp etouffee("a-too-fay")
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet.
Saute chopped onions, bell pepper, celery and seasonings.
(I add Tony Chachere seasoning for real Cajun taste.)
Cook until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and shrimp soup; mix well.
Add cooked shrimp; cook about 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice as main dish.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Set oven at 350°.
Line a deep pan with foil. Dip chicken in melted butter.
Put in crushed Ritz crackers.
Make sure chicken is well breaded.
Put chicken in pan and pour the remainder of butter over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake until brown (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the milk to pudding; mix together.
Add Cool Whip to pudding; mix together. In an 8-inch flowerpot, layer mixture (cookies, etc.), ending with cookies on top.
Add flowers and gummy worms (if you like).
Serve with spade.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, refrigerate over night.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown the ground beef. Drain excess grease and place in crock-pot. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together. Cook on low setting 5 to 6 hours or high setting 3 to 4 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and add cocoa; stir good.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs and add the vanilla and mix all together. Add the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork; form into ball.
Before serving, top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken (save chicken broth for sauce following) with celery strips, a few bay leaves and a little onion.
Then skin and bone the chicken.
Set aside.

title: rita's taco soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in a little oil until tender. Add beef and cook. Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 45 minutes to 1 hour. May add water if soup is too thick.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into ball.
Put parsley and pecans on plate; roll salmon ball on plate.
Serve with Melba toast or Ritz.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed; let cool. In punch bowl, crush half of cake. Add half of prepared vanilla pudding, then 2 bananas (sliced), then 1 can pineapple (drained), then 1 can cherry pie filling. Repeat second layer same as the first. Top with Cool Whip. Chill.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, vanilla, 1/4 cup sugar and water and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat all ingredients together, except bananas and honey, on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl. Add bananas and honey.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into cake pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or golden brown.
Frost if desired.

title: shrimp and bay scallop marinara
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil. Add tomatoes, basil and parsley. Simmer 25 minutes, uncovered.
In a separate saucepan, heat vermouth until just about boiling. Add shrimp and scallops. Boil until shrimp turn pink and scallops turn white.
Add seafood with vermouth to tomato sauce and simmer. Serve over linguini and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in medium size pan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Boil for 8 minutes.
In another pan, mix chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
After mixture has boiled for 8 minutes, pour into Marshmallow Creme.
Cream all together until thick.
Pour into large pan; cool.
Cut into desired squares.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Take above and blend with complimentary fresh fruit or canned fruit (drained).

title: apple cream pie
directions: Put 1/2 of mixture into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate the rest.

title: southern turnips
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Drain well; remove bay leaf. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add turnips, potatoes, salt, pepper and red pepper; toss gently.
Spoon into serving dish; sprinkle with parsley.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: snow punch
directions: Beat together mashed bananas, lemon juice and sugar.
Chill good.
Pour banana mixture into punch bowl.
Stir in cream. Slowly pour in 7-Up.
Float spoonfuls of lemon sherbet on punch.
If desired, sprinkle flaked coconut on top.
Makes about 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: cheese roll
directions: Place softened Velveeta on wax paper and cover with another sheet and roll between to about 10
Remove onto sheet of wax paper and cover cheese with softened cream cheese (up to about 1 inch).
Sprinkle chilies over this and roll length wise.
Use a knife to start rolling.
Crimp edges with a fork.
Transfer to saran wrap (easy to roll onto the saran) and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
This will last a long time when refrigerated.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Set crackers aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour mixture over crackers to coat.
Stir or shake.
Ready in 2 hours.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Bake cake following package directions.
I make two tiara pans and one 9-inch round pan.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red-eye gravy
directions: Fry ham in oleo over low heat; remove from pan.
Stir sugar into drippings until dissolved, stirring constantly.
Add coffee, stirring well.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: classic chocolate layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together cocoa and boiling water in small bowl until smooth; set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour milk to creamed mixture.
Add reserved cocoa mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and ham.
Mix with cream cheese.
Add Accent and Worcestershire, then mix again.
Roll into a ball and chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: caramels
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup, butter and 1/2 can milk.
Bring to boil.
Add balance of milk slowly as to not stop boil.
Stir to 248° on a candy thermometer.
Keep boiling slowly.
Turn heat off. Add wax and nuts.
Pour into buttered pans.
Let sit.
Score to cut.
Wrap individually or place in small cupcake holders.

title: chow chow
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and onions.
Remove seeds from peppers and chop.
Mix all ingredients in a large cooker and cook until tender.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes 15 pints.

title: streusel caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup of butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts. Reserve 2 cups.
Press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile in saucepan over low heat, melt caramels, milk and remaining butter.
Pour over prepared crust.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix corn bread, onion and squash.
Add celery, soup and margarine.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish for 45 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Place sherbet (slightly thawed) in punch bowl.
Add can of pineapple juice.
Begin pouring ginger ale into bowl.
Continue to pour until bowl is full or bottle is empty.
Great for any gathering.

title: lemon-dill chicken(microwave recipe)
directions: Place margarine in rectangular dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch). Microwave, uncovered, on High 20 to 30 seconds until melted. Arrange chicken breast halves, thickest part to outside edges of dish in margarine.
Cover tightly and microwave 4 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cover apples with sugar and let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix together flour, oil, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla. Stir in apple/sugar mixture. Add nuts and coconut (if coconut is not used, add an additional 1/2 cup nuts). Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled red onions
directions: Place onions in a 1-gallon resealable plastic bag.
In a medium bowl whisk next 5 ingredients.
Pour vinegar mixture into bag and seal.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Using a slotted spoon, place onions in skillet and cook until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugars and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs and blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually, blending well.

Form into soft balls and place about 3-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross pattern. If dough is too soft to flatten without sticking to fork, chill dough.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin crumb cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, eggs, milk, cinnamon and salt together. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of mixture, then sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted butter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.
Let cool. Cover with whipped topping, if you wish.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Combine ground beef and onions; roll into balls.
Brown meat. Take meatballs out of skillet.
Stir flour into drippings; brown. Stir in water until thin.
Return meatballs to gravy.
Let cook about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bran muffins 7 week
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients in bowl; let cool. Add oil to first mixture when it is cool. Measure 2 cups All-Bran to use later. Mix next 6 ingredients together; add to first mixture. Add 2 cups All-Bran by hand. Cover and refrigerate. Spray muffin tins with Pam. Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in pineapple liquid.
In a saucepan, cook pineapple, cornstarch mix and drained pineapple.
Cook until clear.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add coconut, walnuts or pecans. Pour in prepared graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked ziti supreme
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat. Stir in pasta sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and macaroni.
Spoon into 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chafing dish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form balls about 1-inch size. Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: tinker's 7 layer casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of baking dish; add corn, salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 the tomato sauce over corn and rice.
Add in layers onions, bell peppers, green beans and ground beef.
Add remainder of tomato sauce and top with bacon.
Cover lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover and continue to bake 30 minutes longer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavorings.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend well and chill for several hours.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: recipe for a good member
directions: Blend together and form into one being.
Serve generous portions to everyone you meet daily.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer 1:
Mix 1/2 stuffing with melted margarine and spread on bottom of dish.

title: fresh strawberry freezer jam
directions: Remove stems from strawberries and crush, one cup at a time using a potato masher. Combine berries and sugar in bowl. Stir and set aside for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. In a saucepan stir pectin and water together on high heat. Stir the pectin mixture into the fruit mixture. Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved and is no longer grainy, about 3 minutes. Pour quickly into jars to within 1/2 inch from the top. Wipe off edges and cover with lids. Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours to set. For immediate use. Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks. Freeze remaining containers up to 1 year. To use, thaw in refrigerator.

title: strawberry lemonade slush
directions: Puree strawberries in blender. Combine sugar, 1 cup water and lemon juice; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add remaining water, pureed berries and a few drops of red food coloring. Serve over crushed ice with berry and lemon slice floaters.

title: cheese and sausage grits
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add garlic, salt and pepper; set aside.
Cook grits according to package directions; add to sausage.
Stir in cheese, butter, eggs and chilies; mix all well. Pour into a well buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: country style cole slaw
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add the next 4 ingredients; toss well.
Cover; chill for several hours.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix with cream cheese and sauerkraut. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll into balls.
Dip in egg-milk mixture, then roll in bread crumbs. Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: weight watchers stew
directions: Brown ground beef and completely drain off grease (I wash mine through 2 waters).
Put everything into pot and cook until done. Put some Sweet 'N Low to taste in.
Very low in calories and fat.

title: caramel cooked icing
directions: Cook in a large thick pot the sugar, milk, butter and soda to a soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and beat on high until it begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
If you beat it too long, set the bowl in a pot of real hot water and it will soften back up.

title: peppermint icebox dessert
directions: Roll vanilla wafers until fine.
Mix with softened butter. Put half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down firmly.
Whip the cream until stiff and add to marshmallows (small ones or large ones, cut up).
Add pecans and crushed very fine peppermint candy. Stir until thoroughly mixed and spread over vanilla wafer crumbs. Cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill thoroughly or overnight.

title: makes-its-own-crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased (I use Pam) 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less.
The center will appear rather soft.
Properly done, it will have a delicate crust over the top, sides and bottom.
It will be solid enough to cut after it has cooled.
The center will be a perfect cream pie.

title: vodka sauce
directions: In frying pan, cube Prosciutto and saute in 2 tablespoons butter until browned; add vodka (flame vodka for 10 seconds).
Put remaining ingredients in pot.
Be sure to break up tomatoes and all juice; heat.
Add Prosciutto and juice from frying pan.
Cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 3/4 to 1 pound pasta.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; let cool completely.
Split layers. Mix together the sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Set aside 1 cup for the frosting; put remainder between the layers.
Blend the reserved sour cream mixture with the Cool Whip; frost cake. Store in airtight container in refrigerator for at least 3 days before serving.

title: swedish stew
directions: Pour last 2 ingredients over first 5.
Don't stir.
Bake 3 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: homemade cake
directions: Cream Crisco, egg yolks and sugar.
Add flour, milk, baking powder, beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Makes 4 or 5 layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use any filling.
Ice with buttered icing.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 8 minutes.
Pour into a 13 pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, chocolate squares, evaporated milk and margarine and cook at a rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow creme vanilla and nuts.
Grease a cookie sheet and put wax paper on top of cookie sheet.
Pour fudge onto cookie sheet.
Score candy before cooling.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut fudge. Use the wax paper to help remove it from pan and put in your favorite container.

title: bean soup
directions: Put all this in a large pot at once and simmer until beans are soft.
Add:

title: berry syrup
directions: Use Sure-Jell and double the amount of juice called for in the jelly recipe.
Add syrup and sugar called for plus 1 cup.
Make according to jelly recipe.

title: butterscotch cake frosting
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Place pan in cold water and beat until smooth.

title: orange sherbet dessert
directions: Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved.
Add cold water. Fold in sherbet and orange slices.
Chill.

title: tammy's beans
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes or longer.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: You will need an 8 x 8 pan.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a loaf and place on microwave rack.
Hollow out the center and place a custard cup in the center.
Microwave on High 11 to 14 minutes.
Turn halfway through cooking time.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together 5 times.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix egg whites, salt, cream of tartar, vanilla and almond extract for 3 minutes.
Add 1 1/3 cups sugar and beat 1 minute longer.
Turn to low speed and add flour mixture.
Slowly pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: wendell's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Add chocolate chip morsels.
Place by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash pickles; place in crock and pour cold water and canning salt to cover.
Weight down and let stand 1 week.

title: rigatoni
directions: Saute carrots and onion in olive oil; add ground beef and cook until brown.
Do not drain off grease (there should be very little with the lean beef).
Add tomatoes with juice and tomato sauce; simmer.
Cook rigatoni 14 to 16 minutes in large pot; drain and return to pot.
Add all of the above sauce but 1 cup.
Pour 1/2 remaining mixture in 4-quart casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 Ricotta and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese over and repeat, adding 1 cup of sauce remaining.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ann k's version of poppy seed chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Combine soups, sour cream and chicken and warm.
Mix together 2 tablespoons of poppy seed, crushed crackers and margarine.
Layer about half of the crumb mixture in bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour chicken mixture over crumbs and spread evenly.
Spread rest of crumbs on top.
Sprinkle rest of poppy seed over this.
Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: wet coconut cake
directions: Bake according to directions (use oblong pan) on box.
While cake is still hot, make holes in cake with toothpick and spread condensed milk on top of hot cake.
Top with crushed pineapple.
If cake appears dry, use a couple of tablespoons of pineapple juice. Refrigerate until cold.
Top with Cool Whip and then coconut.

title: ruth's wedding punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water to dissolve. Let cool. Mix all ingredients together, then divide into 2 gallon jugs. Add water to each to make a full 2 gallons.

title: alfredo sauce with mushrooms(salsa alfredo con funghi)
directions: This sauce is for Fettuccine Alfredo.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop wood, carry into house 'n build fire in stove. Get out bowl, spoons 'n necessary ingredients; grease pan 'n empty yeast in warm water. Take doll 'n toys off table 'n give little Lydia a spoon 'n let her help.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over butter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients except flour.
Add flour.
Roll out thick and cut in shapes.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Frost, if desired.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding according to package directions; fold in Cool Whip. Pour over crackers. Top with another layer of whole graham crackers. Gently frost with your favorite chocolate frosting and refrigerate.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt; add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Roll dough in crescent shape.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Add cooled chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Add the beaten egg whites last and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased Bundt pan.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add green chilies and cool.
Add half the shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Mix.
Heat enchilada sauce and tomato sauce, warm to touch.

title: texas tortilla soup(serves 8)
directions: Garnishes:
sour cream, diced avocados, grated cheese.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in microwave, stir until smooth, add peanuts and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper to harden.
Vary chocolate chips and peanuts depending on your taste.
Peanut may be substituted with Rice Krispies.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Mix with whipped cream. Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Add layer of pudding mix, then crackers, until all pudding is used and ending with graham crackers.
Spread chocolate icing on top. Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: crunchy flounder fillets
directions: Combine
mayonnaise
and next 2 ingredients.
Spread on both sides
of
fillets
and
coat
with crushed corn flakes. Place fillets
on rack of a lightly greased broiler pan.
Bake at 400° for
to
minutes or until fish flakes easily. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: fresh tomato, cheese and herb tart
directions: For the crust, combine the flour and salt in a food processor. Add butter and cut in, using on/off turns, until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add enough water by tablespoons to form moist clumps. Gather dough into ball.
Flatten into a disk. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Roll out dough to a 13-inch round. Transfer to an 11-inch tart pan with removable bottom. Trim edges. Freeze crust 15 minutes.
Line crust with foil and fill with dried beans or pie weights. Bake at 375° until crust is set, about 15 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cover tomatoes with water and boil for 15 minutes.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Place in sterile jars and cover with hot lids.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, water, and sugar.
Boil until berries "pop".

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan 28 crumbled Oreo cookies and 1 stick oleo.
Mix cream cheese (softened), 1 cup confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cookie mixture.
Mix until thick, both boxes of pudding and 3 cups of milk.
Spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Top with more Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate shavings or crumble more Oreos on top.

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices, salt and lemon juice.
Add apples; toss to mix.
Roll out pastry; line pie pan.
Trim off overhang.
Roll pastry for top; cut vents near center.
Add half the apples; pack well.
Dot with butter.
Add remaining apples. Moisten rim with water.
Adjust top crust.
Leave about 1/2-inch pastry beyond edge; fold it under lower pastry.
Seal rim by pressing together; flute it.
Brush with milk.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue beef yankee
directions: Saute ground chuck; add pepper, onion and everything but barbecue sauce.
Cook until everything is done.
Add barbecue sauce to taste.
Cook until the flavors are even.

title: mama's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in spaghetti sauce, add Tabasco sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Layer as follows in oblong dish.
Cover bottom lightly with sauce.
Put layer of noodles (about 5) and another layer of sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and Romano cheese, then put a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with next layer.
Top with a layer of Mozzarella cheese slices.
A layer of cottage cheese may be added with the layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix crackers and 1 stick margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan (10 x 4-inch). Beat sugar and butter in a large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Beat into sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk until well blended.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Spread in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let stand and cool 20 minutes and glaze.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In saucepan, warm applesauce.
Add margarine; let melt.
When hot, stir in soda; stir until foamy. Stir well and mix into dry ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Add nuts or dates, if you like.
Grease tube pan and pour mixture into it.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Spread dough in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix and pour over pastry.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Toss apples in mixture and spoon apples over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400°.
Bake 25 minutes. Cool before removing from pan.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt. Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer; remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Immediately remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into a baked and cooled 9-inch pie shell.
Add coconut (I mix it in).

title: vegetable soup
directions: In 3-quart soup pot, saut onion, celery, carrots and cabbage in olive oil about 10 minutes, stirring often. Add garlic, zucchini and mushrooms and saut 10 more minutes. Add chicken broth, tomato juice and parsley flakes. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Add spinach, salt, pepper and lemon juice. Simmer 15 minutes. Serve and enjoy. Makes 6 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed on box.
Brown beef in Dutch oven
or
heavy
skillet.
Add salt, garlic and pepper. Cook slowly, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: "lizzies"
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by the teaspoon.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Dredge cherries and pineapple in flour before combining with other ingredients.
A delightful holiday cookie.

title: world's best potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 1/2 hour more at 350°.
(For lower fat, substitute 2 cups plain yogurt, not vanilla, for the sour cream.
For variety, substitute cream of mushroom soup and/or cream of celery soup for 1 or 2 cans of potato soup.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops with italian sausage sauce
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Brown well on all sides in oil in a large skillet.
Remove chops.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons pan drippings.
Remove casing from sausage and brown lightly.
Crumble meat in skillet.
Mix in onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring until onions and sausage brown lightly.
Mix in garlic.
Return pork chops to pan.
Spoon sausage mixture over them.
Pour in broth and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Boil.
Cover. Reduce heat.
Simmer until pork chops are tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve chops with sauce spooned over.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Note:
Do not use electric mixer when making this recipe and do not overbake.
You will also need foil (midget-size) baking cups.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing for approximately 30 minutes. Lay chicken in ungreased baking dish.
Lay onion and pepper on chicken pieces and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange angel food cake
directions: Slice the cake once, Pour 1/2 cup orange juice over the cut sides and poke with a fork.
Let stand while mixing: 3 cups sour cream, 4 tablespoons, orange juice, 6 tablespoons sifted powdered Sugar.
Spread on the cut side, replace top and cover all. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon grated orange rind over all.
Put into freezer and remove 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Remove membranes from grapefruit.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water and sugar.
Mix well.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix in grapefruit sections and nuts.
Pour into baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Refrigerate until set.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Crumb in blender 15 seconds.

title: tastes like champagne
directions: Mix grape juice and ginger ale.
Serve chilled.
This makes a wonderful party punch...always a hit!

title: best beets
directions: Cook whole beets until tender.
If baby beets, leave whole, otherwise slice, then cover with the sauce.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix in a small saucepan:
Brown Sugar, Cornstarch, & Salt. Stir in:
Crushed Pineapple with Syrup, Lemon Juice, and Prepared Mustard.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 1 minute. 30 minutes before the Ham is done, remove from the oven, pour off drippings.
Score the Ham, dot with whole Cloves and brush on the Glaze.
Ham is to be baked at 350 until done.

title: quick hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger until well done.
Drain.
Add manwich.
Cook until boiling.
Add chopped Jalapeno pepper to taste.
This dip is better when the flavor and hotness of the Jalapeno is evident. Serve with Nacho chips or Frito Scoops corn chips.

title: quick gumbo-style beef sausage soup
directions: In a large saucepan combine first six ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until okra is tender, stirring occasionally.
(Do not overcook okra.)
Stir in pepper sauce.
Place 1/4 cup rice in four individual soup bowls. Ladle equal amount of soup into each bowl.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix as any other cake.
Start with a cold oven and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: In 3 teaspoons bacon fat, cook onion, celery and green pepper until very soft.
Add potatoes and barely enough water to cover. Add salt.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add clams with liquid, mushroom soup, milk and marjoram.
Simmer.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over chowder when served.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Skin and debone chicken.
Dip in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Brown at 350° in an electric skillet in margarine for 3 minutes each side, until brown.
Lay sliced pepper on top.

title: broccoli-bacon salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix vinegar and sugar together.
Add Miracle Whip.
Stir together.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss to coat.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: new banana cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans or a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.

title: philadelphia n.y.-style cheesecake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter; press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: chunk-style applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover; cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve warm.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper. Add tomato paste and recommended water and simmer over low heat. Stir occasionally.
Cover tightly.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes. Put on a good hot dog!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix baby food, oil, sugar, eggs and chopped nuts.
Mix ingredients together until mixed well.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon to above ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Cut up hard-boiled eggs; set aside.
Beat soup until smooth.
Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over Chinese noodles.
Serves 8.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger. Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce. Remove from heat.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add thoroughly beaten eggs.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls and place in ungreased pan.
Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Dough may also be cut out if desired.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
(I bake mine at 350°, you have to watch them very closely.)

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In bowl, stir eggs, syrup, sugar, chocolate, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chili
directions: If too thin, add tomato paste or more beans.
If too thick, add tomato sauce.

title: spaghetti
directions: Boil water with salt, then add spaghetti.
Lower flame and mix frequently (so it does not stick together).
When soft, pour in strainer and rinse with cold water.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Make a layer of half the beef, about 1/2-inch thick in bottom of greased baking pan.
Cover meat with stuffing mixture.
Cover with remaining ground beef.
Combine mushroom soup and onion soup mix and spread over top of meat.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and food coloring.
Let set for 4 to 5 minutes.
Fold in sour cream, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into fingers and bake on greased cookie sheet at 250° until bottom is brown or 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add milk and wafers.
Blend in coconut and vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach (pear) cobbler
directions: Arrange drained, sliced peaches in 10-inch square baking pan. Pour on lemon juice.
Spread brown sugar over peaches.
Sprinkle on cinnamon.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Form into 12 balls.
Drop in soup mixture and simmer approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken lemon
directions: Dip each slice of chicken into flour, then egg.
Fry in hot peanut oil; brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and put on paper to drain.

title: brown sugar bites
directions: Cut bacon into thirds. Wrap each sausage with a third of a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick. Place in a baking dish in a single layer. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 375°. Serve warm. Makes about 48.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Saute onions in oil until golden brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and use as sauce with favorite toppings. Makes enough for 2 to 4 pizzas, depending on how much sauce you prefer.

title: best ever chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Let stand about 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently. Chill. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: franks and potatoes casserole
directions: In microwave, bake potatoes for 10 minutes on High.
Let cool. Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick; reserve.
Prepare sauce:
In a 2-cup measure, whisk together the soup and milk.
Stir in the pepper and thyme.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 minutes or until slightly hot and starting to bubble, stirring once.
Slice the franks; place half the slices in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Add the peas, potatoes and 1/2 cup sauce.
Top with 3 tablespoons crumbled potato chips or corn flakes.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes. Serves 4.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except Kisses.
Roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Place unwrapped Kiss in center of ball.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Heat until warm. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat on high 2 minutes. Stir in enough flour to make soft dough. Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning in grease. Cover. Let rise in a warm place.
Let rise until dough has at least doubled in size. Divide dough and place in separate bread pans. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy blueberry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell and chill 1 hour.
Add blueberries.
Best if fruit is chilled.
May use any type of fruit filling.

title: fudgies
directions: Mix ingredients and beat until smooth.
Freeze in ice cube trays or special popsicle containers.

title: vegetable soup(low calorie)
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley in a large stockpot. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Remove 3 cups of vegetables and broth and puree in blender or the work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Return puree to pot, add parsley and reheat. Serve hot.
Serves 9; 1 cup per serving.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Put half of the batter in greased pan.
Spread pie filling on top.
Thin the remaining cake batter with milk.
Pour on top of filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon plus sugar mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cookie bites
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt over hot water the chocolate bars; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes.
In small bowl, beat eggs and salt at high speed until thickened, 3 minutes. Add brown sugar and beat at high speed until thick, about 5 minutes.
Beat in cooled chocolate and vanilla until smooth.
Drop onto greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes; cool.

title: t.r.'s a cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing at medium speed on an electric mixer until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into ball and roll into nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn relish
directions: Drop ears of corn into boiling water; boil 5 minutes; remove. Dip in cold water.
Cut from cob and measure 10 cups.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars to within 1/2-inch from top of jar.
Seal tightly.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: curry chicken divan
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients. Layer a 9x12 dish with cooked chicken, then cooked broccoli. Pour soup mixture over layers. Cover with grated cheddar cheese and 1 cup bread crumbs. Dot with margarine.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese, gelatin and Cool Whip in a bowl.
Fold in sliced strawberries.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together with spoon.
Cook broccoli with stems until just slightly firm.
Microwave boneless, skinless chicken.
Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Layer broccoli, then chicken.
Pour mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice. (May make up and refrigerate overnight, then bake until heated through.)

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add to the corn and melted butter.
Beat well.
Drop
by spoonful into deep fat for frying. Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour, mixing before adding buttermilk, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
These pies will freeze well.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured heavy-duty (cast-iron) frying skillet.
Bake for 1 hour in oven preheated to 350°.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: caesar dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add mayo and mix.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.
Will thicken.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage at 236°. Remove from
heat;
add
chocolate
chips, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until chocolate is melted and blended. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add tomato paste and 1 can of water. Simmer 15 minutes. Butter 3-quart casserole dish. Cut up cabbage in bottom layer. Add ground beef mixture for second layer. Add rice as third layer. Add tomatoes. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Remove cover; turn off oven and let set awhile. Top with cheese.

title: make ahead sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Generously grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cook sausage until brown; drain well.
Arrange bread to make a "crust" on bottom of pan.
Spoon sausage over bread; sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs and half and half to salt.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover casserole with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: craft clay
directions: Mix ingredients together in a saucepan.
Stir until smooth texture.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
The mixture will resemble mashed potatoes.
Pour out and allow to cool.
When mixture is cool, it can be kneaded and food color may be added, if desired.
You are ready to mold, shape or roll and cut with cookie cutters.
After shapes are dry, they can be painted.
Clay may be stored in refrigerator in airtight container and then warmed to room temperature or used immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Quarter squash the longway and cut into 2-inch lengths. Parboil until slightly underdone.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Grate Longhorn cheese.
Slice onion.
Alternate layers:
squash, onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: brunch punch
directions: Combine bananas and fruit juice concentrate in blender until smooth. Combine banana mixture, pineapple juice, water and sugar in mixing bowl. Mix well. Pour into freezer containers or mold and freeze. Thaw until mushy. Add carbonated beverage. Yields 6 quarts.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix in 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Put in crust and chill for 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Chill condensed milk.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and let stand until cool.
Beat condensed milk until thick.
Add sugar and fold into Jell-O.
Line pan with crushed pineapple.
Pour Jell-O mixture over pineapple and top with graham cracker or vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: clams and linguine
directions: Boil water for pasta.
In large pan, mix clams, garlic, hot pepper flakes, parsley, white wine and oil.
Bring to boil, then simmer until clams shells open.
Drain pasta, then toss with clams.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, if desired. Serves 2 to 4.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: No matter who the child may be

title: peanut butter cups
directions: With electric mixer, mix margarine and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir in crumbs and knead mixture until well blended.
Press mixture in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over peanut butter mixture.
Melt chips by placing in a 350° oven for about 2 minutes, then spread chocolate evenly.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, butter and corn syrup in pan for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over corn.
Spread on cookie sheet and place in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes. Cool.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Stir in water. Bring to a boil and cook.
Stir constantly until thick (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, then return egg mixture into pan.
Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon peel and butter.
Slowly stir in lemon juice.
Cool to lukewarm. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix everything together, except apples and nuts (do not use mixer).
Add apples and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated white beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and let drain.
Dice green onions and celery.
Add rest of ingredients.
Marinate overnight.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cora salad
directions: Use juice from pineapple and apricots to make 1 3/4 cups. Cook pudding and juice until thick and clear.
Cut up the fruit and add the cooled pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Wipe zucchini with damp cloth and cut off top.
Slice zucchini and parboil it.
Take slices and place each piece in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add melted butter to each slice; sprinkle generously each slice with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake in 350° oven until a little brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, rice, soup and 1/2 cup onions in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap; vent.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Microwave cheese spread according to label directions.
Stir cheese spread into broccoli mixture. Top with remaining onions.
Microwave 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: ham and cheese roll-up
directions: Remove
crescent
roll
dough from container carefully. Do not separate,
leave
in a rectangular shape.
Spread with mustard, then thin slices of ham; top the ham with thin slices of Swiss cheese.
Roll
up
(jelly
roll
fashion)
from
the longest
side of
rectangle.
Slice
crossways into about 3/4 inch
slices. Place
on
cookie
sheet sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake
at 350° until done.
Can be stored in refrigerator and reheated in microwave if any left over.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix a little of the string bean juice with the soup to make it a little more juicy.
Mix with string beans and pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for half an hour.
Spread French fried onion rings over top and broil just until they begin to sizzle. Watch closely so they don't burn.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Lightly cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with shredded cabbage.
Add a layer of meat mixture.
Proceed with layers, ending with a light layer of cabbage.
Mix last ingredients together.
Cover cabbage and meat layers with this mixture.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° or until cabbage is tender.

title: quick and easy pork chops(by dr.  golden)
directions: Cook pork chops on one side, then turn.
Place an onion next to the pork chop, then a teaspoon of ketchup and then a slice of lemon.
Cook until done.
Best to do in an aluminum pan on the grill or in a pan in the oven.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine the apple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and sweetener. Set aside.
Fill crust of pie shell with apples.
Pour juice mixture over all.
Dot top with margarine.
Place crust on top. Cut slits.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Bake cake as per instructions on box in a baking dish.
Mix the sugar and pineapple with juice and boil 3 minutes.
Punch holes in hot cake and pour this mixture over the cake while it's hot.
Now beat powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo.
(Add pecans.)
Spread on cake while it is still warm.

title: tomato bread
directions: Cube bread; put in pot.
Add tomatoes, sugar and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Let boil a little while, a minute is enough.
Remove from stove and add oleo.
Stir and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Beat egg, milk and oil with fork.
Make well in flour; pour in milk mixture.
Stir with fork until ingredients are moist but lumpy.
Add blueberries. Spoon batter into greased muffin tins (or use cupcake cups). Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Place asparagus in bottom of buttered casserole dish; cover with chicken.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops; place in shallow pan.
Mix bread crumbs, onion, margarine, water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: In a large, oval baking pan with tight cover, cut a piece of heavy duty foil (shiny side out) and line pan with it, allowing enough to fold back over meat.
Place brisket (fat side up) in pan and cover with barbecue sauce and water.
Arrange foil snugly over brisket and bake for 4 hours at 350° without peeking.
Remove from oven.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Beat until thick. Add whipped cream and chill 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups strawberries to mixture.
Pour into pie shell and garnish with remaining strawberries.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown meat.
Combine remaining ingredients, except sauerkraut. Mix well and pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, basting 2 or 3 times.
Add sauerkraut and continue at 350°, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Cook, uncovered, for an additional 15 minutes.
(Total cooking time is 1 3/4 hours.)
Great with baked potatoes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil for 1 minute.
Add vegetables to the hot liquid.
Add the oil.
Heat just until vegetables are hot; remove from heat.
Let cool; store in a covered dish.
Will keep for weeks.

title: oven crisp chicken strips
directions: Add garlic to melted margarine.
Combine corn flakes, flour and Hi Ho's.
Dip cut, washed, salted chicken into margarine mixture, then into corn flakes mixture.
Place in ungreased baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 5.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: In large saucepan over high heat, bring water to a boil.
Add nuts and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Rinse nuts under running hot water; drain.
In large bowl with rubber spatula, gently stir warm nuts with sugar until dissolved.
Heat oil in a deep frypan until 350°.
Add 1/2 the nuts and stir until light brown.
Strain or cool on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Cook remaining nuts the same.
Cover tightly.
Will keep well, 6 to 8 weeks.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saut the onion and carrots in the oil.
Add the water and chicken bouillon cubes until cubes are dissolved (about 15 minutes).
Add the noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat until smooth. Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well.
Press half of it into bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup walnuts and chocolate pieces over crust and top with caramel mixture, spreading to edges.
Top with teaspoons of remaining cake mix and press into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle rest of nuts.
Press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool and cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sawdust pie
directions: First Layer:
Place crushed vanilla wafers in pan.

title: cornish hens
directions: Stuff birds with grapes. Tie legs together.
Place in 500° oven until brown.
Mix mushrooms, sherry and soup; spread over birds.
Cover and bake approximately 2 hours at 325°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs separately, beating well after each.
Add coconut and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and cook at 350° until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Tang and juice from fruit and vanilla pudding.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Pour over fruit and chill.
Add sliced bananas before serving.

title: famous yam balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes, sugar and pineapple together.
Take large marshmallows, put potato mixture around it using your hands and roll in coconut.
Place in buttered dish.
Continue until mixture is used up.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: creole steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2 x 2-inch strips and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in slow cooker with onions, celery, tomato juice, Worcestershire, garlic powder, wine, dry mustard and sugar.
Cook on high setting for 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and mushrooms. Cook on low setting 6 to 8 hours.
This recipe can be modified for stove top cooking.

title: my favorite onion casserole
directions: Put layers of onions in casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and cheese together.
Pour over onions.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: extra creamy dried beef dip
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in beef, bell pepper and onion.

title: creamy frozen lime pie
directions: In a small to medium mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and evaporated milk; beat until smooth.
With mixer on medium speed, add lime juice and beat for 1 minute.
Pour into pie crust; freeze for at least 2 hours.
Let stand for 10 or 15 minutes at room temperature before cutting into 6 servings pieces.
Garnish with any blueberry sauce or syrup.

title: peanut crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, salt, butter and peanut butter.
Beat eggs into mixture.
Sift together flour and soda. Blend into sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate bits and peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake 9 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Cool on rack. Yields 9 dozen cookies.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Bring water and lemon to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Rinse with ice cold water.
Peel and devein shrimp; place in a large bowl or gallon size Ziploc bag.
Combine remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Beat with a wire whisk. Pour over shrimp and toss.
Cover.
Chill 8 hours.
Drain shrimp; serve in a lettuce-lined bowl.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with crescent rolls.
Spread with mustard; set aside.
Saute together for 10 minutes the zucchini, margarine and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients into zucchini mixture.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey pasta salad(low cholesterol)
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Cool.
Combine cooled macaroni with remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill. Serves 7.

title: noodles
directions: Mix
ingredients, turn out on lightly floured board and knead about
5 minutes.
Roll out thin.
Let dough stand until dry.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Drop into boiling water and boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Great to add to soup.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix well in 3-quart dish. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and blend all other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake for 50 minutes at 300°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour butter into mixture and mix, then pour into greased pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: cherry or apple pie for microwave
directions: Mix together and roll out; put in pie dish.
Pierce pie crust and bake on High for 4 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Grease a 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish.
Put half of bread cubes in bottom.
Add the rest of the ingredients that have been mixed together.
Top with the rest of the bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients into blender; pour into cups and serve.

title: pralines
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook on high heat for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Remove from heat.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine
flour
and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for
15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, eggs,
cinnamon, allspice and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Blend until
smooth.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle with
reserved topping.
Bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes. Cool
before cutting
into
bars.
Makes
32 (1 x 2-inch) bar cookies.

title: spiced apple drink
directions: Melt cinnamon candies in apple juice.
Add brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon.
Stir well.
A dash of nutmeg and allspice can be added.
Heat and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook ground beef and garlic. Stir. Blend in water, onion soup, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, sugar, pepper and oregano. Stir well.

title: oklahoma oatmeal bread(my friend corenna's aunt eva's)
directions: In
a
large
bowl, mix together well the milk, oil and vinegar.
Add the oats, flour, sugar, soda and salt and again, mix well.
Dredge raisins and nuts in a bit of flour and stir in last.
Pour
into
a sprayed or greased and floured (I use Baker's Joy)
x
x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 (7 x 4 x 2-inch) loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until center tests done. (Aunt Eva lived in Oklahoma!)

title: cherry delight(makes two pies)
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese, milk and sugar and pour into crust.
Sprinkle other ingredients over mixture.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Fold in beaten egg whites.
Mix and bake in greased and floured pans at 350° until done.
When cool, ice with filling for strawberry cake.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: In large pot, add lima beans, soup, soy sauce and water.
Let simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.
Then add cooked pork chops to mixture. Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve over hot rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Arrange half of broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole. Cover with peas. Mix other ingredients for sauce (except crackers) and pour half over peas and broccoli. Add rest of broccoli and then rest of sauce. Cover with Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy crock-pot chicken
directions: Layer rice and soups, ending with chicken breasts on top. Cook on high for 2 hours or low for 4 hours.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Stir until smooth; add lemon juice and rind.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff, last. Bake in unbaked pie crust at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs.
Beat until thick.
Fold in pineapple and bread.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Bake with foil; remove last 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.

title: macaroon squares
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in the crumbs, chocolate bits, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Line bottom of an 8-inch square pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread with meringue mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares (or serve slightly warm with vanilla ice cream).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes at 400°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening (have shortening melted and warm, not hot).
Take 1 1/2 cups flour and beat into mixture with spoon.
Put in rest of flour and work with hands until it is of a smooth texture.
Sit in warm place and let double in size.
Work down and cut rolls.
Let raise again and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: snap salad
directions: Combine beans, onions, oil, 1/2 cup vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Next day, drain beans.
Mix remaining ingredients except bacon.
Toss beans and bacon together.
Make well in center of beans and fill with egg mixture.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Simmer first 6 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Cook shell macaroni al dente.
Drain macaroni and set aside.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, lightly coat the bottom of the pan with a little of the meat and mushroom sauce.
Layer half of the macaroni.
Layer half of the meat sauce on top of the macaroni, then layer half of the sour cream on top of the meat sauce.
Repeat layers of remaining macaroni, meat sauce and sour cream.
Top with Provolone and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wax beans and green beans. Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove and sprinkle cornstarch over to thicken.
Return to oven for another 1/2 hour.
Add wax beans and green beans, about 1 hour before serving.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat the potatoes until smooth.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
If too stiff, add milk.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Season with garlic salt. Dot with margarine and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, melt butter.
Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well and press on bottom of pan. In a medium bowl, mix Eagle Brand, sour cream and lemon juice. Spread over crumbs.
Spread pie filling over creamy layer.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; mix nuts and cinnamon and sprinkle over pie filling.
Serve warm or cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: enchiladas
directions: In a medium pan brown chicken.
Add onions and completely cook.
Add both soups and cook until creamy.
Add 1/2 can chilies. Spoon 2 to 3 spoons of meat mixture into taco shells.
Add 2 pinches of cheese.
Roll up.
Place into a baking pan.
Spoon remaining meat mixture over the top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and chilies on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: beef taco mac
directions: Cut beef steaks lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips, then crosswise into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium/high heat until hot (not boiling).
Add beef and onion. Cook and stir 3 minutes and season with salt.
Stir in taco seasonings, tomatoes, pasta and water into beef.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes or until pasta is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: best ever patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushroom soup.
Form into patties and fry.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with soup diluted with 1/2 cup of water or milk (I use 2 cans of soup).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no-bake oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil all but peanut butter and oats for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: french oven stew
directions: *Can use can of mushrooms or can of frozen onions.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Place in large casserole or baking dish (2-quart or larger).
Brown meat and onion.
Drain and add to macaroni.
Add soups, water and juice from mushroom pieces.
Brown mushrooms and add to mixture.
Add packet of seasoning and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: fish-flake croquettes
directions: Mix fish flakes with seasonings; add to white sauce and chill thoroughly.
Mold into croquettes; roll in cracker crumbs.
Dip into slightly beaten egg and roll in crumbs again.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) about 3 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 medium croquettes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: reese cups in a pan
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press in 9x12 pan. Cover the top with Hershey bars or melted chocolate chips.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator; minimum 6 hours.
Drain eggplant and place in pan.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions, green pepper, and celery in melted butter until tender.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Chop up lettuce and add tomatoes, onion and beans.
Just before serving, add hamburger meat, cheese, Fritos and dressing.
This does not keep so eat it all up!

title: hot apple cider
directions: Choose amount to make.
For single serving, place juice or cider in mug or cup; heat in microwave to desired temperature. Garnish with cinnamon, nutmeg or mint, if desired, and serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions, put in bottom large casserole 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with vegetables.
Spread 2 c. of undiluted soup over vegetables.
Top with cheese and cover with tater tots.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute together the first 6 ingredients.
Mix together the Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Layer sauce, noodles, cheese and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch crunch cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add the next 5 ingredients.
Add oatmeal last.
Add chocolate chips.

title: bachelor biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin tins with Pam. Mix flour, mayonnaise, milk and salt.
Drop into muffin tins and bake for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and sugar tube pan. Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 80 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick; boil about 10 minutes. Cool; add mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup and picante sauce in a large dish.
Cover bottom of dish with flour tortillas shells. Mix cheeses together.
Pour half of meat mixture over shells.
Put half of cheese over mixture.
Put another layer of shells and meat mixture.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Add rest of cheese.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening with fork or pastry blender until it is the consistency of small peas. Sprinkle with ice water, blending with fork.
It may require more or less water.
Divide dough into small pieces; roll each on floured board.
Lay 5-inch saucer on dough and cut around it. Place 1 tablespoon of the filling on the dough; fold over so filling is evenly distributed.
Press edges gently with fork, but do not puncture dough.
Put about 2 inches of oil or shortening in large skillet.
Heat to 365°.
Cook 1 or 2 pieces at a time. Brown on one side, then turn and brown the other.
Drain.
Yields 11 or 12 pies.

title: ned's low calorie in between pick-me-up
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients until foamy.
Then add vanilla extract.

title: pasta siciliana
directions: Brown ground beef in oil and then season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic powder and parsley.
Then drain and set aside.
Salt eggplant and have it weighted down for 2 hours.
Squeeze out excess water and fry up small amounts until light brown and crisp.
Set aside.
(Drain well on paper towel.)

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Boil sugar and cherry pie mix together for 7 minutes. In a separate pan, boil 2 cups water and add cherry pie jello mix. Combine both mixtures; add pineapple with juices and pecans (optional). Pour into jello mold. Refrigerate until firm. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: easy stew
directions: In a
large
roasting pan combine 4 soups and mix well. Add beef and
stir
again.
Cover.
Bake
at 350° for 3 hours. Add carrots
and
bake 1 more hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
You
can	also
add peas, baby onions and mushrooms the last hour.

title: stir-me-nots
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
After butter is melted, sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter, then coconut.
Sprinkle on chocolate pieces. Pour condensed milk evenly over all ingredients in dish.
Top with nuts.
Do not stir.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into desired pieces.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Mix above ingredients in a saucepan and cook slowly for at least 30 minutes.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Place in a large bowl.
Cover cucumbers and onions with cold water and add 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain for 15 minutes.
Dissolve the sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Put in freezer bags and freeze.
To use, simply thaw in refrigerator.

title: indian stew
directions: Cook hamburger meat and add everything else and cook until rice and potatoes are done.

title: baked hamburger dish
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
At same time, brown 1 pound hamburger with a little onion.
When browned, add tomato soup, water, beef bouillon, molasses and A.1.
Stir and add corn and macaroni when cooked.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or microwave on High for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer onion in butter. Cook broccoli according to directions on package. Drain and reserve 1/4 to 1/2 cup liquid. Combine liquid and remaining ingredients and add to broccoli mixture. Add more milk if needed. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: light strawberry cake
directions: Make cake mix according to box directions.
