To make frosting, add 6 tablespoons of water to sugar and bring to a boil until sugar makes ball in glass of water.
Add sugar liquid to beaten egg whites; beat until real firm.
After cake is cool, poke holes in cake and pour some of juice from strawberries.
Frost cake; then add sliced strawberries between middle layer and on top.
Let cool for at least 1 hour in icebox before serving.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and Eagle brand milk until Kool-Aid is well mixed.
Add Cool Whip and fold in until well mixed.
Pour into crust and chill.
If adding fruit, fold in last, before putting mixture in the crust.
Try drained pineapple with orange Kool-Aid, or drained black cherries with black cherry Kool-Aid.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Add jello.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions.
Beat cream cheese with milk.
Mix all together in mixer.
Put in mold to chill.

title: strawberry glazed pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries; drain thoroughly.
Arrange 2 cups of the whole berries over the bottom of baked pie shell.
Crush remaining berries and put in a saucepan.

title: busy day stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Place all ingredients in a large covered pan.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours or until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: I cut the pepper, onion and celery in 1-inch pieces and slice cucumbers 1/2-inch thick.
Mix the sugar and Italian dressing together; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, stir and serve.

title: st. patty's day cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, oil, eggs and carbonated beverage. Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Evenly pour in batter; bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add orange sherbet as needed. (Depends on how much sherbet you like in punch.)

title: chilli
directions: Brown beef and onions and drain.
Mix ketchup, tomato paste, sugar, vinegar and chili powder in with beef mixture.
Add 1 quart of water.
Bring to a slow simmer and add beans.
Cook for at least 1 hour.
Serve with saltines, Ritz crackers or over cooked rice.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In large saucepan cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stri in chicken broth, chicken, tomatoes, beans, corn and red pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Add okra; simmer about 5 more minutes or until tender. In small jar add flour to cold water; shake well.
Stir into stew mixture.
Cook over medium heat until it boils and thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Yields 6 servings.

title: french toast
directions: Mix egg substitute, milk and flavoring in a bowl and dip the bread in to soak up the mixture.
Grill on a griddle sprayed with Pam.
Serve with syrup, fruit or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate beer kraut cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in vanilla.
Sift together cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add egg mixture alternately with beer, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in chopped sauerkraut.
(If kraut is mild, don't bother rinsing in water, just drain).
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool on wire racks.
When thoroughly cool, frost with chocolate sour cream frosting by Pillsbury or mocha whipped cream or plain cream.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: afternoon tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and mint and let steep for 10 minutes, strain.
Stir in sugar until it melts, add frozen juice and water to taste.
Serve with fresh sprig of mint.

title: oven chicken croquettes(serves 4)
directions: In a medium size saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons of butter over medium heat.
Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 to 2 minutes without browning.
Gradually whisk in milk and broth and cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat; let cool for 5 minutes.

title: sour cream softies cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter until creamy.
In separate bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add alternately to sugar mixture the flour mixture and sour cream. Mix thoroughly.
Place tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mix.
Let cool and set.

title: ham 'n cheese flips
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Set aside.

title: herbed cheese
directions: Place the cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Add the Feta by forcing it through a coarse sieve.
Set the cheeses aside at room temperature for 30 minutes to soften.
Beat the cheeses until well combined.
Add the garlic, chives, tarragon, thyme, rosemary, salt and cayenne.
Beat to blend thoroughly.
Place the bay leaf into the bottom of a 1-quart plastic container or 3-cup ceramic crock. Spoon in the cheese, packing it down tightly.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 days before using to allow the flavors to meld.

title: stuffed squash italian
directions: Prick squash several times with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until tender; cool slightly.
Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Set shells aside.
Drain pulp; mash.

title: macedoine salad
directions: Arrange shredded lettuce on salad plates.
Mix vegetables with French dressing.
Put a spoonful on each plate and serve.

title: sausage a la creole
directions: Place sausage and water in a skillet.
Cover and boil 20 minutes over medium heat.
Uncover and let water cook out.
Fry to a golden brown.
(Do not prick with fork or other sharp instrument, as this will cause meat to be dry and lose juices.)
Add onion and cook for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: quick casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and place in bottom of large casserole.
Place sliced potatoes on top of meat.
Pour soup and water on top; season with salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: mocha bars
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in jelly roll pan.
Cool and cut into small squares.
Frost with remaining ingredients using enough milk for spreading consistency.
Roll in crushed peanuts.

title: quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together. Blend in Cool Whip.
Stir well until blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Beat well and cool slightly. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat well.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350° in preheated oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Whip the cream cheese with fork.
Add all ingredients, except 1 cup of pecans; mix well.
Roll cheese ball in remaining pecans. Store overnight in aluminum foil.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and slice into even rounds 5 medium potatoes.
Put in salted ice water until ready to use.
Generously butter an 8-inch pie plate.
Drain and dry the potatoes thoroughly and arrange them in the pie in a circle with the rounds overlapping.
Pour melted butter over each layer, using at least 1/4 pound, salting lightly and peppering generously.
Continue until dish is full.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake potatoes until crusty and brown.
Invert on round platter and cut like a pie.
Serves 4.

title: derek's homemade chili
directions: Cook beef until lightly browned.
Drain off fat.
Add onions, green peppers, and seasonings.
Cook stirring occasionally, until soft.

title: susan's spicy beef dip
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in skillet until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, sugar and oregano.
Cover and simmer gently 10 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat and remove from heat.
Add cheeses and heat and stir until cream cheese is melted and well combined.
Keep warm in chafing dish or fondue pot.
Serve with crackers or party rye. Makes 3 cups.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Mix ingredients; simmer in a saucepan over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently, or microwave 7 or 8 minutes, stirring once.
Let cool.
Pour over meat (deboned chicken breasts, link sausage or steak).
Marinate overnight or for at least 4 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour tins (2 loaves). Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with any brand nondairy whipped topping.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on 5 (10-inch) flour tortillas; roll up and chill.
Slice; make about 50 slices.
If desired, serve with salsa.

title: gourmet dressing
directions: Pour vinegar into cruet; add salad dressing mix and shake well.
Add salad oil and tomato juice.
Shake.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine and mix other ingredients.
Cook in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Stir in paste and seasoning; simmer while preparing muffin pans.
Place biscuits in each greased muffin pan, pressing to sides and bottom.
Spoon 1/4 cup of meat mixture onto biscuits; then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yield:

title: original fun chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in Fun Chips or M&M's.
Place by level teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: To prepare artichokes, cut off pointed tips and cut stems so that artichoke sits flat in a large pot.
Wash in warm water, drain, turn upside down and tap on cutting board to open flower in order to stuff.

title: mother fox's meat sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients and cook on medium heat.
Simmer as desired.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Brown the chicken in skillet about 5 minutes each side (skin side first). Sprinkle onions and garlic, then paprika, over top and stir.
Add chicken broth; cover.
Simmer about 10 minutes or until the chicken is done.
Remove chicken to warmed serving dish.
Blend sour cream and flour and stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, about 1 minute.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: pecan pie
directions: Brown pie crust a little.
Cream brown sugar and margarine. Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Divide between crust and bake for 15 minutes at 400° then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: marian's lo-fat meatless chili(lite recipe)
directions: Saute the vegetables; add to beans and chili mix.
Cook on low heat for one hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except shell.
Mix together well and put in shell.
Cool and serve.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Chop onion; saute in margarine until golden brown.
Cook rice. Mix soup with Cheez Whiz.
Cook broccoli.
Mix Cheez Whiz, soup and broccoli together.
Add cooked onion.
Mix together with rice. Pour into casserole dish; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until warm (35 to 45 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Stir all ingredients except raisins in pan with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in raisins. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf, pressing gently to loosen.
Remove from pan.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding, the pineapple and the juice.
Add Cool Whip and some marshmallows.
Put in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Pour dry ingredients into large bowl and mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then remove.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Mix together the pie filling and pineapple in cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Slice the oleo over top. Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: juanita's cheese dip
directions: Add all ingredients to a large crock-pot. Cook on high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 2 to 3 hours. Stir after first hour and again later until all cheese is melted.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Place shortening, onion and mushrooms in large skillet.
Cut steak; add to skillet and brown.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Cover tightly.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Before serving, blend in 1/2 cup dairy sour cream.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter with electric mixer.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread into pie shells and chill.
Whip cream until stiff.
Blend in powdered sugar. Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Spread this mixture on top of base mixture and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking pan with cooking spray. Combine all dry ingredients, mix well.
In medium bowl whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until cake springs back.

title: oven fried parmesan chichen
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley; mix well. Dip chicken in butter; dredge in cracker crumb mixture.
Place chicken on greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for one hour.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Put all ingredients, except oil, in blender or mixer.
Beat thoroughly.
Add oil very slowly while beating on high.
Again, beat thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Shelf life is about 2 weeks.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: In large bowl, toss sugar, flour and cornmeal lightly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Beat with rotary or electric mixer until smooth and thoroughly blended.
(Mixture may be a bit lumpy.)
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.

title: bacon-vegetable stuffed peppers
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Reserve drippings.
Prepare cornbread, using bacon drippings; bake.
Saute onion in small amount of bacon drippings.
Crumble cornbread; add to onion-bacon-tomato mixture.
Mix well.
Clean and halve green peppers.
Stuff bacon-bread-vegetable mixture in raw peppers. Serves 8.

title: harvest apple cake
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over chopped apples.
Pour sugar over the chopped apples and stir well.
Let stand for 30 minutes, then, sift all dry ingredients (mixed beforehand) together and add to apple mixture.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add oats, peanut butter, margarine and pecans.
Thoroughly mix together. Drop on wax paper.
Let cool, then enjoy!

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven at 325°.
Mix brown sugar, butter and egg; then stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet, cool slightly.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Mash cream cheese with fork into gelatin.
Let cool but not jelled.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well. Put in salad (if you desire).
Refrigerate until firm.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak into strips. Heat oil. Add strips and cook until brown on high heat. Drain off oil. Pour small jar of soy sauce in with meat and cover meat completely with water. Cook at a slow simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, making sure water is always covering steak.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for twenty minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir the ingredients once when mixture begins to thicken to prevent the corn from sticking on bottom of casserole. Serves 6.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well. Chill for 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: cream corn
directions: Cook for 4-5 hours in crock pot on low. Will feed 15-20 people.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Set oven at 250°.
Spray large shallow roasting pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread popped corn evenly in pan.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
In melted butter, stir in sugar, syrup and salt; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn; stir with a wooden spoon.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool completely.
Break apart into clusters.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Blend together butter and sugars.

Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture and mix well. Add vanilla. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts, if desired. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned around edges. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserving half of the dried beef, mix all ingredients.
Form a ball.
Roll ball in the reserved dried beef to coat well.
Serve with crackers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, lime juice and whipping cream in a bowl with mixer until stiff. Fold into pie crust. Refrigerate 2 hours and garnish with lime slices before serving.

title: deep dish fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in deep dish and let cool.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together and pour on top of melted margarine, but do not stir.
Pour peaches all over the top of the sugar, flour and mix mixtures.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cool and colorful rainbow salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: marinated fresh vegetables
directions: Wash and seed all vegetables; cut into chunks.
Place into bowl.
Pour dressing over.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: golden hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown ground beef.
In casserole dish put ground beef; put cooked macaroni over beef.
Layer with tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper and top with golden mushroom soup.
Cook on High in microwave for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate or cocoa, butter and black coffee together in medium to large saucepan.
Remove from fire.
Dump in sugar and stir until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add sour milk or sweet milk with vinegar added and vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, until thoroughly mixed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Frost as desired.
Makes three 8-inch or two 9-inch layers or 1 large sheet cake.

title: mocha cheesecake(microwave)
directions: Microwave butter for 30 seconds on High.
Combine butter, cookie crumbs and sugar.
Press in bottom of 8-inch round micro-safe pie dish.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes; cool crust.
Melt chocolate in dish for 2 minutes.
Microwave cream cheese until soft.
Combine chocolate, cream cheese, eggs, sugar, coffee and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over cooled crust. Microwave at Medium for 14 minutes or until center is set.
Turn dish twice during cooking.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: soubise
directions: Boil
rice for 5 minutes.
Drain. Peel and chop onions. Heat butter and oil in baking dish.
Stir in onions and rice. Cover pan and place in preheated oven at 325°.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: apricot cake
directions: Combine cake mix and jello together in large bowl.
Add milk, egg yolks and margarine.
Beat batter until smooth.
Add mashed apricots and pineapple flavoring; stir.
Beat egg whites until fluffy; fold in batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cornstarch and cocoa until thick or comes to boil.
Cool.
Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and evaporated milk with mixer.
Mix all together and pour into container.
Fill with plain milk to container 3/4 full.
Freeze.
This is for a 6-quart freezer.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Boil all ingredients for 2 minutes, stirring at all times. Cool and beat by hand until the right consistency to spread.

title: chicken divan
directions: Thaw broccoli on paper towel and press out excess fluid. Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with broccoli.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Mix together and spread over chicken, mayonnaise, cream of chicken soups, curry powder (optional) and lemon juice. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Melt butter in a 9 1/2 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom.
Insert 1 clove in each pineapple chunk.
Place clove side down in butter mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Shape into loaf.
Place on top of pineapple.
Set inside large baking dish to catch drippings.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Invert onto platter to serve.
Yields 6 servings, about 365 calories each.

title: chili dip
directions: Simmer all together for a couple of minutes.
Just before serving, add 1/2 pint of whipping cream.
Reheat.
Place on giant Fritos.

title: nut balls
directions: Makes a small batch, better to double it.

title: spinach and mushroom salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach; discard stems.
If leaves are small leave whole.
Toss spinach, mushrooms and eggs together in a salad bowl.
In a small bowl, mix oil, sugar, lemon juice, mustard, pepper and salt; beat well.
Pour over salad and toss until all leaves are coated.
Serves 6.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Cut rind up and let stand in cold water overnight.
Next morning, cook until clear in same water.
Make syrup; tie spices in a bag.
When the syrup gets thick, drop in drained rind and let come to a boil.
Take out fruit and drain.
Next morning, heat syrup; pour over fruit.
Let boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip chiffon cake
directions: Sift together into mixing bowl first 4 ingredients.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add next 4 ingredients. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.

title: the best blueberry muffins
directions: Beat oil, sugar, orange juice, rind and egg together.
Combine dry ingredients and add to batter, stirring only enough to moisten.
Batter will be very thick.
Fold in blueberries quickly without excess stirring.
Bake in greased or paper cup lined muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and cover with sugar.
Let stand several hours, usually overnight.
Cut grapes in half.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: lorna doone pie
directions: Melt butter.
Crush cookies.
Add melted butter to crushed cookies until well blended.
Press cookie mixture into 2 pie plates.
Mix pudding with milk; then add pudding mixture to softened ice cream.
Beat together until smooth.
Put into freezer until hard.
Place Cool Whip over pudding and ice cream mixture.
Crumble Heath bars and sprinkle over top.
Keep in freezer.
(I freeze it firm before covering it up.)
Makes 2 pies.

title: danny's pea salad
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
Drain and put into a medium size bowl.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Don't add the peas unless you like peas.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll rolls.
Place in a 10 x 15-inch pan; allow to go up the sides.
Bake 6 minutes at 325° until light brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread over cooled crust. Combine vegetables after they have been cut up small and sprinkle on top of pizza.
Sprinkle with cheese and lightly press down. Chill until ready to serve.

title: homemade italian spaghetti sauce and meat balls
directions: In a large kettle, add all of the ingredients.
Turn stove on medium.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, shape into 1 inch balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for
20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat butter or margarine in 1/2-quart bowl with electric mixer at low speed until smooth and creamy.
Beat in sugar gradually until fluffy.
Mix chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating 3 to 5 minutes.
After each addition, spoon into shell.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Add eggs to this mixture.
Add flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° in preheated oven.
Place kisses in center of cookie while hot, pressing them in gently.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add salsa, corn and chili powder.
Place 1 cup crushed Tostitos chips on bottom of casserole dish. Top with beef/salsa mixture.
Cover with the mayonnaise, cheese and 1 cup crushed Tostitos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomato and sour cream. (Make a double batch for a 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll at once in confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll again.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Melt butter; pour over bread crumbs and toss.
Heat tomato puree with water, salt and brown sugar.
Simmer about 5 minutes. Pour mixture over crumbs and toss; put in casserole dish and bake covered at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hasselback potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice thinly within 1/4 inch of the bottom so that the potato will stay intact in the oven.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
May add grated Swiss cheese and bread crumbs, if desired.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and spices; stir.
Add plum, oil, eggs and nuts; stir.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: chocolate cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift cocoa with flour and add slowly to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: pineapple oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; beat.
Add eggs; beat.
Add pineapple, oats, flour, etc. and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine and drop from a teaspoon in hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: overnight biscuits
directions: Place yeast in warm water; set aside.
Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add yeast mixture.
Cut in the shortening.
Add milk; stir until well blended.
Pour onto floured wax paper.
Roll out; cut out biscuits.
Place thin biscuits in pan.
Place wax paper between layers.
Place in refrigerator.
Can be kept for 1 week and taken out as needed.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 24 biscuits.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Divide ingredients into 2 balls, then work each ball into long roll about 1-inch thick.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice very thin.
Put whole pecan half on top of each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100 rounds.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes two loaves.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Crush chips and make one cup.
Mix ingredients well and form into small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: old-fashion coconut cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients thoroughly with mixer for at least 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder, then add egg whites, milk and vanilla.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 deep 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 360° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden.
Add tomatoes and chicken. Mix flour and chili powder with enough water to make a paste.
Add to chicken mixture to thicken.
Add olives and salt.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Soon after cake is removed from oven and still warm, make punctures with toothpick or sharp knife.
Pour a blend of cream of coconut and condensed milk over entire cake. Allow cake to cool for 2 hours.
Frost with a mixture of Cool Whip and Angel Flake coconut.

title: rancho beans
directions: Mix all ingredients; heat and simmer.
Pour in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Great at cook-outs.

title: lemon cheese bundt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the margarine, butter and cream cheese. Add 2 eggs, 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar.
Mix on low speed until blended. Repeat until all ingredients are blended. Add extracts and blend.
Pour batter into a prepared Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: Put the last 4 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, or a rolling boil for 1 full minute.
Remove from the heat.
Add cocoa and mix.
Add the vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Spread evenly on ham slices.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Chill, tightly wrapped in refrigerator.
Serve sliced with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Place 3 or 4 cups raw apple slices in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 cup of water over apples.
Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Cover with cake mix.
Melt oleo and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown. Frozen or canned apples may be used.

title: cucumber frost
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in hot water; add vinegar and onion. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise, blending thoroughly.
Fold in cucumber, mixing well.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Remove skin and bones.
Place chicken in bottom of large Pyrex dish.
Mix together soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Do not stir.
Mix together chicken broth, margarine and stuffing mix.
Spoon over mixture already in pan and bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Can use 2 cans chicken soup instead of 1 mushroom soup.

title: custard pie
directions: Brush inside of pie shell with slightly beaten egg white.
Add sugar, salt and milk to eggs.
Strain and pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with a few grains of nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, oleo and salt in a large saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda; it will get frothy.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Put on 2 cookie sheets. Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: fudge square
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl, then add eggs and shortening.
Mix well.
Add walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wendy's shish kabobs
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer. Let stand for 2 hours.
Cut peppers and onion into large pieces. Combine all ingredients into large bowl and marinate beef and vegetables overnight.
Alternate meat and vegetables onto skewer. Grill or broil until browned.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel and seed enough zucchini to make 2 cups when cooked and mashed.
Mix all ingredients well and put in a pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes at 350° for 1/2 hour until knife comes out clean.

title: six layer dish
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Layer ingredients in order given in a 2-quart greased casserole, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over one tablespoon of brown sugar and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: mrs. walker's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each egg.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Sift other dry ingredients, except soda.
Work enough flour in gradually to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan over medium to low heat, melt marshmallows and margarine, stirring frequently until smooth.
Stir in gelatin; remove from heat.
Add popcorn and peanuts to marshmallow mixture; stir gently until coated.
Stir in chocolate chips.
With greased hand, shape cooled mixture into balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cover hamburger with cold water and cook until red color disappears.
Stir often.
Add all ingredients and cook slowly for 2 hours or longer.

title: harvest slush
directions: In plastic pail, mix first four ingredients. Cover and freeze. Before serving, allow to thaw 15 to 30 minutes.
Pour mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale, mixing well.
Yields 30 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut toasted bread into 1/2-inch cubes. Saute onion and celery in butter 2 minutes. Add beef and saute, stirring constantly until browned. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add to meat. Heat thoroughly.
Fold in bread cubes.
Fill peppers with hot mixture.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake in a greased shallow baking dish at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook additional 5 to 10 minutes at 400° to brown tops.
Serves 4.

title: noodle one-dish dinner
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in large mixing bowl, mixing well. Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish, patting down for smooth top. Cover amply with cheese; cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: quiche laredo
directions: Coat a 9-inch glass pie pan with nonstick spray; sprinkle peppers evenly over bottom of pan, followed by cheese.
Combine eggs and picante sauce and add to cheese mixture.
Let sit for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili and tamale bake
directions: In a casserole dish, layer unwrapped tamales, then chili.
Add grated cheese and corn chips.
Bake at 350° until warm through and through and cheese is melted.

title: sopapillas(fried biscuit puffs)
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Gradually add the water, stirring with a fork.
Dough will be crumbly.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead into smooth ball.
Divide in half and let stand 10 minutes.
Roll each half into a 12 1/2 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares (do not reroll or patch dough).
Fry a few at a time in hot fat until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with honey or roll in sugar and cinnamon. Makes 40.

title: chicken madrid
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in 1 tablespoon oleo until soft.
Stir in Velveeta, olives and mushrooms.
Stir.
Add cooked noodles.
(Cook noodles in 3 cups chicken broth until broth has been absorbed.)
Add mushroom soup and all other ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: valerie's meatless chili
directions: Cut the onion and green pepper into small/medium size cubes (depending on your taste).
In a large pot, heat the vegetable oil.
Once hot, put in the onion and green peppers and saute. While still in the pot (on low heat), put in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste and kidney beans.
Stir around a bit.
Now add in chili powder, cumin, seasoned salt, mustard, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir well.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until beans are tender).
Good with rice, spaghetti or just by itself. Especially good with sprinkled Cheddar or Parmesan cheese.
Will make 6 servings.

title: sauce for sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in 10-inch skillet. Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make 2 1/4 cups.
Stir juice, water mixture, vinegar, catsup and soy sauce into skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: momma's orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Baste chicken with butter and season with garlic powder and pepper.
Place chicken on aluminum foil in pan.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Next, pour frozen orange juice, soy sauce and parsley flakes over chicken. Bake for another 45 minutes.
Use the juice as gravy.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in small amount of water.
Reserve liquid.
Make white sauce of flour, butter, broth and milk. Coarsely chop broccoli in blender in its own liquid; add to cream sauce.
Heat thoroughly, adding milk to consistency desired. Complement the soup with 1 of the spices listed.
Serve with croutons.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Drain peas; rinse with cold water and drain well.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Combine oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and cayenne pepper; mix well.
Pour over peas.
Stir gently. Allow to chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
At serving time, add the diced tomato.
Mix carefully.
Serve as a relish with meats or garnish with lettuce and a spoonful of mayonnaise and serve as a salad.

title: deep dish chicken pie
directions: Slice margarine in bottom of 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish. Mix flour and milk; pour over margarine.
Combine first four ingredients and pour over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salsa black bean salad
directions: Great summer side dish. Can be made in 5 minutes if you're putting together a last minute meal.

title: calico casserole
directions: Brown the bacon; drain and set aside.
Brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain meat and onion, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle bacon crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in a 2-quart casserole.

title: curious cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cake mix and 1/3 cup milk.
Press 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with 1/2 cup milk.
Put nuts and chips on top of cake mixture.
Pour caramel mixture over this.
Press remaining cake mixture gently on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Put grapefruit, oranges, cranberries, drained pineapple and apples in large bowl and toss.
Add bananas just before serving.
(Large enough for company.)

title: finger paints
directions: Add enough water to flour and soap flakes to make thick and slippery consistency.
Add food coloring.
Roll up your sleeves and have fun!

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Add margarine to mix until coarse crumbs, reserve 1/2 cup crumbs. Spread remaining in bottom of greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Combine Eagle Brand and peanut butter. Spread over cookie crust, add remaining crumbs on top and M&M's. Bake 20 minutes more.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Drain pimientos; combine liquid with beef, oats, soup mix, dry mustard, egg and milk.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place on edge in loaf dish.
Between each patty, place 1 slice of onion and some pimientos, reserving 1/2 jar for garnish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Top with cheese and reserved pimientos.

title: bev's chocolate fudge
directions: Bring to a boil: sugar, milk and chocolate and boil 7 minutes.
Remove and add butter, vanilla, marshmallows and nuts. Beat until thick.

title: dangerous brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix as directed on the package.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts, stirring until moistened.
Follow baking instructions on brownie mix box.
Enjoy!

title: rolls
directions: Scald
the
milk
and
mix in the shortening and sugar, stirring
until
sugar is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 package
yeast
and
enough
flour to make a cake-like batter. Let rise about 2 hours in a warm place.
Stir down and add the salt, baking powder and soda.
Add enough flour to now form a stiff batter.
Roll out, cut and let rolls rise until double. Bake in moderate oven, about 350° until done.
Makes 90 to 95. This is an old recipe. It always turns out good for me.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a paste. Trim the crust off 3 pieces of bread. Butter lightly and make 3 slices of each piece. Slice bacon strips in half. Spread cheese mixture on bread and roll with bacon on outside. Hold together with 2 toothpicks. Cut each in half between the toothpicks. Broil until browned on one side, turn and brown other side. Makes 18 yummy appetizers!

title: stuffed chicken cutlets
directions: Dip cutlets in egg, then cover with bread crumbs.
Lie cutlets out and spread cream cheese/allouette mixture over cutlets.
Roll up and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella when almost done.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour together.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks. Stir in cocoa.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Stir constantly to prevent burning.
Add vanilla after cooking mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue. Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Add flour to eggs.
Add sugar slowly to eggs and flour.
Beat in vanilla and Milnot, salt and Butterfingers.
Place in freezer. Can finish filling freezer can with milk to fill line.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and Cool Whip.
Stir in canned fruit.
Fold in bananas.
Keep frozen.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cheese and pimento sandwich spread
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients together.
Cook remaining ingredients. After thickened, cool slightly and add ground ingredients.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, mix and boil for 1 minute the sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
After coming to a full boil, remove from heat.
Stir in oats and vanilla.
Mix well, but don't stir too long.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper until cool.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa and stir.
Add milk and butter.
Do not stir!
Heat on High for 3 minutes.
Stir real good.
heat on High for 3 to 4 additional minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until smooth and pour into buttered pan.
Chill, cut and serve.

title: prospector's beans
directions: Combine beans, Worcestershire sauce and thyme; set aside.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bean mixture, tomatoes and onions, ending with a layer of beans.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours. Check occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together, reserving part of cheese to sprinkle on top. Put in greased casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Add salt to egg whites and beat until mixture forms soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy.
Slowly add Karo, beating thoroughly after each addition until firmly peaked.
Fold in vanilla.
Tint with food color if desired.
Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: breakfast special
directions: Place bread cubes on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread sausage on top.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Mix eggs, salt, mustard and milk until well blended.
Pour mixture over all; cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Add butter to hot mashed potatoes and stir until melted.
Stir in milk, sugar, eggs, salt and cinnamon.
When blended, pour in 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake about 35 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice and mix with other ingredients. Add back 3 tablespoons of the pineapple juice.
Pour ingredients into a casserole dish and top with crunched corn flakes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Start cooking syrup and peanuts on low heat.
Keep syrup bubbling low; add all other ingredients, except soda.
Cook until syrup is honey colored (about 15 minutes).
STIR OFTEN.
Take off of heat and stir baking soda in real good.
Have a buttered cookie sheet already greased.
Pour the candy on sheet and spread out level on sheet.
Let cool for about 1 hour.
It should come out of pan easy in solid pieces.
Take a hard object and break as desired.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hello dolly pie
directions: Pour chips into crust, then pecans.
Top with coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add milk, water and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boiling. Cook 5 minutes longer.
Cool and stir in vanilla.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Crush Butterfingers and set aside.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and egg yolks.
Then add Cool Whip to sauce mixture and mix well.

title: streit's matzo balls
directions: Mix well.
Add matzo meal and stir thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Form into balls and drop into soup or into 1 1/2-quarts of boiling water into which 1 tablespoon salt has been added.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together real well.

title: microwave easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young. Allow extra time for training for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle while others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet and tender by garnishing with patience.
Wrap in charity and keep warm with steady devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Shelf life is forever.

title: fruit salad with instant pudding
directions: Put pineapple chunks with juice and fruit cocktail with juice in 2-quart bowl.
Drain oranges.
Cut up apples, bananas, cherries, pecans and other fruit.
Add to other fruit mixture. Sprinkle pudding over top and stir.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: svensk livets brod
directions: Mix 3 cups unbleached flour, wheat flour, water, sugar and yeast into bowl.
Beat in egg.
Combine milk, brown sugar, salt and chicken fat into a pan and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add milk/chicken fat mixture to flour/yeast mixture.
Add remaining unbleached flour (sifted) to mixture and stir until satin consistency.
Knead dough.
You may add cinnamon and sugar to dough.
Can be made into rolls or loaves.
For loaves, grease pan and let rise to 1-inch from top.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes and reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.
Do not overbake!
Remove immediately from pan and let cool.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine milk, butter, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and cheese; mix well. Spread in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Slowly cook onions in saucepan until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large skillet over high heat, melt margarine; add onions and saute for 1 to 2 minutes; add shrimp and saute until shrimp turn pink.
Mix gravy according to package directions.
Add gravy and tomatoes (with juice) to shrimp mixture.
Stir well.
Add hot sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve over rice.

title: eylene's salad ring
directions: Boil soup. Add cheese; stir until smooth. Add dissolved gelatin. When cool, add vegetables and mayonnaise. Put in mold; chill 3 hours. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise and paprika. Recipe may be doubled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and water for 8 minutes and drain, then mix the other ingredients with the broccoli and put into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta banana nut cake
directions: All dry ingredients are sifted together.
Measure buttermilk, vanilla, bananas (mashed), eggs, nuts and shortening (softened). Mix with dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.

title: pie crust
directions: Place flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut Crisco in and mix so it is in small pieces.
Mix beaten egg, water and vinegar into mixture.
Toss lightly with fork.
Divide into 4 portions.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
Roll out to size of pie pan.

title: salmon soup
directions: Saute celery, onion, pepper and garlic in margarine until onion is translucent. Add potatoes, carrots, chicken broth and seasonings. Simmer 20 minutes. Add corn, salmon and evaporated milk. Heat thoroughly and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings. Freezes well.

title: pedernales river chili
directions: Place meat, onion and garlic in large pan.
Cook until light colored.
Add oregano, comino seed, chili powder, tomatoes, hot pepper sauce (Tabasco), salt and hot water.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla. Beat until combined.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or test for doneness.
Cool cake and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: maple glazed apple cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: frankie's egg custard
directions: Cream the butter and add sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and salt.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° until crust browns around edges.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Take out of oven just before you think it is done (Grandma Jones' instructions), about 1 hour.

title: kuchen
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In bowl add butter and, with pastry blender or two knives, cut into mixture until it is in fine crumbs.
Pat it gently into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes until pale gold.
Combine pie filling and juice; spoon evenly over crumb layer to within 1/2-inch
of edges.
Beat together sour cream, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Drizzle over pie filling, covering most of it.
Bake 20 minutes and cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares.

title: em's yogurt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Beat on medium speed until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cake should look dark brown and crusty.
Let stand in pan 15 minutes.
Remove. Let cool.
Sprinkle with lots of powdered sugar.

title: golden rhubarb jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan, let stand until sugar is almost dissolved.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook and stir until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Cover with paraffin.
Makes 4 pints.

title: large feta lamb pie
directions: Use half of the lemon juice to sprinkle the lamb; set aside. Butter a 2 x 14 x 10-inch baking pan.
Line it with 12 filo leaves.
Put one leave down at a time; spread each one with melted butter.
Top the filo with layer of rice mixed with all other ingredients including lamb.
Lay down another layer of filo leaves using the same method as the bottom layer.
Bake at 250° for about 2 hours.

title: southern cracklin' bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour into a hot greased iron skillet or heavy pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir thoroughly.
Add oil slowly and beat until thick.
Add poppy seed; beat a few minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Mix pkg. of pudding and milk together and chill for 10 minutes. Fold in cool whip. Fold in rest of ingredients and chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together chicken, tomato soup, mushroom soup, chili powder and worcestershire sauce.
Boil chicken broth, chopped onion, chopped celery, chopped bell pepper and butter for 20 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: don't last cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients thoroughly with a spoon.
Combine both of the mixtures (do not beat).
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° in a greased tube pan.
Remove from pan and allow to cool for 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: party lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread in large bowl.
Cover with water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs; mix well.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dice vegetables and add 4 cups of water.
Cook until done. Add seasoning.

title: swirl cobbler pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and liquid until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs. Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl. Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead until smooth.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle fruit evenly over dough. Roll up like a jelly roll. Dampen the edge with water and seal. Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in pan with melted butter and pour sugar syrup over rolls. Bake for 1 hour.
(Any type fruit or berries may be used.)

title: zesty cheese dip
directions: In small bowl of electric mixer, place cream cheese which has been softened at room temperature.
Add Blue cheese, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix at medium speed until well blended. Reduce speed to low and gradually add evaporated milk, mixing until smoothly blended.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: rice dessert
directions: Mix together. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable super soup
directions: In a large pot, place meat and soup bone, water and salt. Bring to a boil and skim.
Add cabbage, onions, carrots, celery and tomatoes.
Cook, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 3 1/2 hours.
Taste for seasoning. Remove meat from soup bone; cut up and return meat to soup.
Cool and refrigerate soup overnight.
Before reheating, skim fat from top.
Serve with loaf of French bread and green salad.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix all well and bake in a large 8 x 12-inch pan at 320° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese; add sugar and beat well. Add eggs one at a time; then add vanilla.
Fold in flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda in a bowl.
Pour boiling mixture over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Stir all together and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: mom's buttermilk popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in muffin or popover tin for 10 minutes, until light brown, in a 350° to 400° oven.
Makes about 16 popovers.

title: old fashion sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift and stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° or 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over cucumbers and onion.
Will keep several days.

title: baked alaska, tropicale
directions: Preheat oven to at least 450°, 500° if the heating unit will do it.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Add alternately with milk and vanilla to egg mixture.
Bake in greased 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Heat until flavors are blended.
Yield:
2/3 cup.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes, cream cheese and butter until cream cheese and butter have melted.
Mix together the sour cream, milk, eggs and onion.
Add all ingredients; beat until light and fluffy.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until light brown.

title: beet pickles
directions: Pack cooked beets into hot, sterilized jars.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; simmer 15 minutes.
Remove cinnamon.
Pour boiling hot liquid over beets, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 30 minutes in boiling water bath or let pressure reach 10 pounds and remove from burner.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: sandy's baked potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in oven and cook for about 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Meanwhile heat water in a large saucepan and add chopped celery to water and simmer until celery is tender.
When potatoes are fully cooked slice down the center and scoop out the inside of the potato.
Add to celery and water.
Add milk, butter, sour cream, bacon, onions, 1 c. cheddar cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Allow the mixture to simmer over low-medium heat until it thickens, Use the rest of the cheese to top and you can also add chives.
Serve hot!!!!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Disregard instructions on stuffing box.
Mix stuffing with margarine only.
Use both envelopes in package.
Cook chicken and remove meat; cut into bite-size pieces.
Reserve broth.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with 1 cup broth and chicken soup with 1 cup broth.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place layer of dressing, layer of chicken, all of mushroom soup, layer of dressing, layer of chicken and all of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in butter about 2 minutes.
Add and stir-fry the asparagus, mushrooms, cauliflower, zucchini and carrot for 2 more minutes.
Increase heat and add the cream, broth and basil.
Boil about 3 minutes to reduce.
Stir in peas, ham and onions.
Cook 1 minute more and season with salt and pepper.
Add the fettucini and cheese, tossing to combine.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: two minute velvet fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and condensed milk uncovered in 2-quart bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla then nuts until well blended.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Split hot dogs; pour barbecue sauce over them.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to product instructions and drain. Cut large scallops in half.
In 3 qt. sauce pan over low heat, melt the margarine.
Add garlic and saute 5 minutes.
Add corn starch, salt and pepper; stir until blended.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook until thickened and boil 2 minutes. Add wine and 1 1/2 cup cheese.
Turn into a 2 1/2 qt. casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring until thawed.
Add undrained pineapple and bananas.
Pour one half mixture into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm, leaving other one half mixture out of refrigerator.
Spread sour cream over chilled layer.
Pour remaining jello mixture over sour cream and chill until firm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook to soft ball stage. Add peanuts and cook until mixture turns dark (300°).
Remove from heat and add soda, salt and vinegar.
Stir well and pour into a buttered cookie sheet. Cool.
Break into pieces.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: goldie's corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate-peanut butter ice-cream pie
directions: Process cookies and peanuts in a food processor until finely crumbled.
Add melted butter, and process until blended.

title: chocolate cake(moist and very easy!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan, combine the first five ingredients and mix well.
Make three holes in the mixture.
Pour the lemon juice in one hole, the oil in the second and vanilla in the third.
Pour the cold water over the top and mix well.
Bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix together; roll in wrappers.
Seal wrappers with water (lightly moistened on edges).
Deep fry to golden brown.
Makes about 30 egg rolls.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown sausage.
Remove sausage and drain, reserving 1 tablespoon fat. Cook onion in reserved fat until tender.
Add beef broth, water, wine, tomatoes, carrots, basil, oregano, tomato sauce and sausage. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Skim fat from soup.
Stir in zucchini, tortellini, parsley and green pepper.
Simmer, covered, 35 to 40 minutes or until tortellini are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: steak skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil, push to side.
Cook and stir onion until tender; drain.
Add enough water to potato liquid to make 1 cup; mix it with catsup, Worcestershire, bell pepper, bouillon, salt, marjoram and black pepper.
Pour on beef and onions.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer (covered) until beef is tender (30 minutes to an hour, depending on meat).
Rinse frozen beans to separate and add with potatoes to meat.
Return to boil, reduce heat, and cook 15 minutes more or until beans are cooked.

title: shipwreck
directions: Fry (but do not brown) ground beef in shortening; drain and add salt and pepper to taste. In large Dutch oven, make layers starting with onions, potatoes, ground beef, peas, and carrots, beef, and kidney beans; add tomato soup last. Bake covered at 300° for 3 hours.

title: egg rolls
directions: Heat wok or large skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons oil until very hot, but not smoking.
Stir-fry ground beef, breaking up meat with spoon for about 5 minutes or until it loses its pinkness.
Add green onions; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove.
Add remaining oil; stir in vegetables.
Add seasonings.
Stir-fry to heat through.
Add fried cabbage and onion.
Mix well.
Put into colander to drain and cool.
Filling should never be used while warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and chocolate together.
Add just enough cold milk to make good paste.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Scald remainder of milk and stir.
Slowly pour into mixture.
Then pour into double boiler and slow cook until thick (hangs on spoon). Then pour into cooked flour pie shell.

title: venison stew
directions: Cut venison in 1-inch cubes.
Roll in seasoned flour; brown in a small amount of oil in a heavy skillet.
Add boiling water and pepper to browned meat; cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add diced vegetables; cook until tender.
Use 2 tablespoons of flour moistened with water to thicken remaining liquid.
Yield:
8 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake using whole egg.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Cream cheese and all 2 cups milk; mix well.
Add instant pudding to cream cheese and mix well.
Pour over cold cake.
Add pineapple over this and then Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with pecans and refrigerate.

title: bonnie's fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken real good. Put self-rising flour in a deep bowl, enough to batter chicken in. Pour enough Wesson oil into skillet so it is half way full. (Iron skillet if you have one.) Turn heat to medium and let oil get hot. Salt chicken and batter real good in flour. Put into frying pan; turn heat down between medium and low. Cover frying pan with lid. This helps to keep chicken moist. Fry until golden brown and turn chicken over to other side. Chicken is done when both sides are golden.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Bake or boil potatoes in their skin until tender.
Cut in half. Scoop out the pulp of the potato and leave the skin to put the mix back into.
Combine the potatoes with the remaining ingredients. Spoon this mixture back into the potato skins.
Place in the oven at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly reheated.

title: best chocolate chip cookie recipe
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat brown sugar, sugar, margarine and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg, beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt, mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minutes, remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together. Spray bread pans with nonstick cooking spray. Pour mix into pans and bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: all in one pork chops
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour.
Dredge chops in seasoned flour.
Brown in oil.
Add 1 1/2 cups water; simmer, covered for 30 minutes.
Add carrots and cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Add water, if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple critters
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, egg and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into lightly oiled iron skillet.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place ingredients, in order given, in top of double boiler. Do not stir!
When margarine has melted, remove pot from heat and stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and let sit for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain
pineapple
and save juice.
Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cut Velveeta into small cubes and mix with pineapple mixture.
Pour
a little juice into this.
Melt butter and pour in half
of
this.
Mix
the rest of the butter with the crushed Ritz
crackers.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and put crackers on
top.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: diabetic pink cloud dessert
directions: Take your can of pineapple plus your juice plus your 2 packages Equal.
Heat and bring to a boil.
Then add your pack of Jell-O.
Then let cool.
Add your cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Fold in 8 ounces lite Cool Whip.

title: stuffed pepper cups(a perky main-dish idea for leftover ham)
directions: Cut tops from peppers.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Chop tops to make 1/3 cup; set aside.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine rice, beef broth, water and salt.
Heat to boiling; stir.
Cover and cook over very low heat for 15 minutes. Cook onion, the 1/3 cup chopped green pepper and the celery in butter or margarine until tender, but not browned.
Stir in ham. Add to rice mixture; toss lightly to mix.
Spoon into pepper cups. Combine bread crumbs and the melted butter.
Sprinkle over tops of peppers.
Place in baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper in a large skillet until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, garlic, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and bring to a rolling boil. Stir sifted flour into water and butter.
Stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Drop by tablespoon onto baking sheet into mounds 3-inches apart.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
In a bowl, add sugar, flour and egg yolks; beat well.
Add butter, juice and rind of 1 lemon and milk.
Beat all this together.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Put into 9-inch unbaked crust and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown and an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate sharp and pimento cheeses.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Roll into 2 large balls or 3 small balls.
Use paprika or chili powder to coat each ball.
May be wrapped in foil and kept in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: old fashion overnight raisin oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine oatmeal and buttermilk and let set overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Yield: 18 pancakes.

title: cola-cherry soda pop(kids section)
directions: Stir the ingredients together and pour this mixture into the molds.
Place the molds in the freezer until frozen thoroughly.

title: gazpacho(a good cold vegetable soup)
directions: Peel tomatoes and coarsely chop.
Peel, slice and finely chop onion.
Seed and coarsely chop bell pepper.
Peel and coarsely chop cucumber.
Combine vegetables in 2-quart pitcher or bowl. Add finely minced garlic if using fresh clove.
Combine tomato juice, vinegar, olive oil, salt, pepper and garlic powder (if used) in small bowl.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill several hours. Serve 1-cup portions.
Makes about 6 to 8 cups.
Contains 64 calories per serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and onion. Drain well.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into 2-cup flour.
Add 1/4 cup flour to water; stir to make paste and pour into first mixture.
Stir, using hands if necessary; roll out on floured surface.
Makes 2 crusts, with enough for lattice topping.

title: pumpkin bread(yield: 3 loaves)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: meat concern
directions: Put corn and tomatoes in a kettle and cook with salt and 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Boil noodles, wash and drain.
Melt remaining tablespoon of butter in skillet and saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms slowly until onion is clear; add celery, meat and pepper.
Cook well; add to corn, tomatoes and tomato soup. Add Worcestershire sauce and taste for seasoning.
Add noodles and simmer all together for 1/2 hour.
Set back and let stand all night in refrigerator, if possible.
One hour before serving, put in a buttered baking dish.
Dot generously with butter and grated cheese (any kind you have), and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 30 minutes.

title: almond berry topping
directions: Combine strawberries, kiwi, sugar, and nectar in small 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and let cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract, almond extract, and almonds. Return to medium heat and continue cooking for about 2 minutes. Pour into a sterilized jar and seal well.
Allow to cool slightly before refrigerating.
Great served over cream cheese.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Add desired amount of butter.
Mix 1 cup of Cheddar, then 1 cup Monterey Jack.
Stir until mixed well.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large casserole dish or round cake pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.

title: pot roast of beef
directions: Pare potatoes and carrots; slice both thinly.
Slice onion. Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Add seasoning and meat to crock-pot.
Add liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).

title: new potatoes in white sauce
directions: Cook potatoes in a 3-quart saucepan, covered with water and salted.
If large potatoes used, cut up in 1-inch pieces, small ones, leave whole.
Drain when cooked.

title: german chocolate thumbprint cookies
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine the first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 13 minutes, or until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Remove from heat; cool.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups of topping mixture; set aside.
In large bowl, combine cookie ingredients and remaining topping mixture.
Stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make indentations in balls; fill with topping mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add whole cranberry sauce and mash into hot liquid.
Add pineapple and juice.
Mix well and pour into mold or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill several hours to congeal.
Really good and sugar-free.

title: sweet pickled peaches
directions: Make a syrup of sugar, vinegar and cinnamon stick. Simmer 15 minutes. Stick the cloves into the peach halves and drop into the syrup. Remove immediately. Delicious with fresh ham. Fix peaches 2 or 3 days ahead.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in syrup, then eggs one at a time.
Beat in flour gradually.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Frost with Chocolate Chip Frosting.
Cut in squares.

title: chili
directions: Cook and drain ground beef before adding other ingredients. Let cook approximately 30 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a mold.
Refrigerate.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: In bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Pour into glasses. Chill and serve.

title: three-layer mexican pie
directions: Brown the beef in a skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain well. Add the beans and seasoning mix and mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Spread the sour cream
over the top. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and spread in jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream chicken with macaroni
directions: Melt butter; add flour, cream cheese, pimiento and seasoning and blend.
Combine milk and chicken broth and add gradually to first mixture, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling and cook for 3 minutes.
Add chicken and macaroni.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: creamy rings and beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together and boil down low. Serve while warm.

title: harvest potato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, covered, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except spinach, salt and white pepper.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add spinach and seasonings to taste.
Heat thoroughly.

title: buttery lemon squares
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and the 1/2 cup powdered sugar until fluffy.
Add 2 cups of flour, beating until blended.
Spread evenly over the bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped nuts.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Combine honey and mustard; mix well.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Pour wine over chicken and sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Cover and bake 45-65 minutes at 350 °
to an internal temperature of 180°.
Serve sauce with the chicken.

title: layer salad
directions: In a 7 x 11-inch glass dish, layer lettuce, celery, onion, peas and eggs.
Combine sugar and mayonnaise.
Spread evenly over dish to the edges.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon or bacon bits. Cover and chill overnight.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/4 cup butter, onion, sour cream (reserve 1/4 cup), pepper, salt, soup (reserve 1/4 cup) and 1 cup cheese. Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together bread, 1/4 cup butter, 1 cup cheese, 1/4 cup soup and 1/4 cup sour cream.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: chocolate cherry torte
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup of crushed cookies for topping.
Combine the remaining cookies with butter.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Add to broccoli and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle the top with cheese.
Melt margarine and add to the stuffing mix; spread on top and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bean soup
directions: Mix all together; put into crock-pot and simmer for several hours.
Serve with hot corn bread or crackers.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Add melted butter to soup; add sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Add dredged raisins and nuts. Pour into greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Blend together soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Stir in broccoli.
Combine crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.
