title: low-sugar fruit jello
directions: Prepare Jell-0 as directed on package.
Mix with applesauce. Pour into 13 in. by 9 in. pan for servings about 1/2 inch thick, or use smaller pan for a thicker layer.

title: chili chicken with cornmeal dumplings
directions: Mix chicken and tomato sauce in Dutch oven. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in corn and beans.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.

title: no-work meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients 2 minutes. Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until pulls away from sides and checks done by inserting a toothpick.
Punch holes in top of loaves and pour glaze over bread in pans.
Remove when cool.

title: very berry sorbet
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar in a saucepan; stir in water.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze 8 hours.
Spoon about 1/4 of frozen mixture into blender or food processor and process until smooth.
Repeat until all the mixture is processed.
Return to freezer and freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops quickly in small amount oil.
Drain beans, reserve juice; place beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or square 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 can mushroom soup to 1 cup bean juice and put in skillet where pork chops have been browned. Warm slightly.
Add 1/2 can onion rings and stir gently to mix. Pour over beans in casserole dish;
then top with pork chops. Cover this with other half of onion rings and remaining 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325° until mixture is bubbly.

title: zesty sauteed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken into 1/4-inch thickness. Mix flour and pepper. Coat chicken with flour mixture.
In skillet in hot oil, brown chicken.
Stir in soup and water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover. Simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry mold(relish mold for thanksgiving dinner)
directions: Dissolve the gelatin and 1/2 cup sugar in the boiling water. Add the lemon juice and undrained crushed pineapple.
Chill until gelatin mixture is partially set.
Fold in the ground cranberries, ground orange, diced celery and walnuts or pecans.
Pour gelatin mixture into an 8 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Drain the pineapple slices; serve salad with pineapple slices.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: double pistachio cake
directions: Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake @ 350 degrees 40 - 45 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil first three ingredients for one to two minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla to the chocolate mixture.
Pour over oatmeal and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto 2 cookie sheet and cool. Makes about two dozen cookies.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets and tender part of stalks into small bite-sized pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss.
Chill overnight or several hours.
For variety, use 1/2 bunch broccoli and small head cauliflower, chopped.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in 2-quart pan and simmer on top of stove for 20 minutes all of the ingredients, except for the catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
After simmering for 20 minutes, add and bring to boil, stirring constantly, the catsup and Worcestershire sauce.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water; set 5 minutes. Add milk, oil, sugar, salt, eggs, and 3 cups flour...rest flour.

title: coconut cream pudding
directions: Melt butter; pour over 1 package of crushed Ritz crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put ice cream in mixing bowl.
Add milk and pudding mix; beat well.
Let sit in freezer for about 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: nutty baked squash
directions: Cut squash in half and spoon out seeds.
Mix all ingredients and spoon 1/4 of mixture into each half.
Place squash in ungreased baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Season cut sides with salt and butter.
Pour water into dish 1/4 inch deep.
Cover with foil and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: male cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares when cooled and cover with powdered sugar.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Wrap each breast half with bacon; secure with toothpick. Place chipped beef in casserole dish, then wrapped chicken breasts.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over meat. Bake in oven at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buffet beef stew
directions: In a 3-quart Dutch oven, cook bacon until crisp; remove, drain and reserve.
Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper.
Brown beef with garlic in bacon drippings; stir in tomato sauce, onions, water, wine, orange peel, oregano, thyme and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add carrots and potatoes; simmer, covered, 30 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes more until slightly thickened.
To serve, garnish with reserved bacon.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly flour pan. Mix egg, margarine and brown sugar. Add vanilla, flour, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Mixture will be thick. Pour into pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Allow to cool, then eat.

title: vegetable marinated salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for at least an hour.

title: peanutty chocolate banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of 2 loaf pans. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine bananas, milk, peanut butter, oil and eggs in small bowl.
Add to dry ingredients; mixing until moistened.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt small amount of butter in pan and brush over chicken. Salt and pepper accordingly.
Combine soups and water in a bowl; mix well.
Pour rice and soup mixture over chicken in a baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.
Check and perhaps stir every so often.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water; cool (put in fridge to speed it up).
Add apricot baby food and pineapple (including juice).
Mix well.
Combine milk, cream cheese and nuts.
Mix until smooth.
Add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and chill to set.
If desired the mixture can be put in two 9 x 9-inch pans (or plastic containers with lids).
Serve one and freeze the other.
Keeps in freezer up to 6 months.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick shells from crabs and place meat in a bowl.
Tear bread into small pieces.
Add all the ingredients to crab meat and mix. Form into 8 patties and refrigerate for several hours until firm. Cook in skillet until brown on both sides.

title: pink lemonade punch
directions: Mix thoroughly in punch bowl the pink lemonade, cranberry juice and ginger ale. Add block of ice or lots of ice cubes, lemon sherbet and strawberries. Makes about 28 cups.

title: apple-oat pineapple bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Stir flour mixture in.
Batter will be lumpy.
If too dry, add milk.
Add pineapple and apples.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or long 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can add nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: elderberry jam
directions: Wash berries, run through Squeezo.
Measure juice; put into 6 to 8-quart pot.
Add lemon juice.
Measure sugar into bowl.
Add box of Sure-Jell and butter.
Bring mixture to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly add sugar to fruit. Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly, and then continue boiling for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off any foam with large metal spoon.
Immediately ladle into jars. Wipe with damp cloth rim of jars.
After cooled, cover with wax.

title: crunchy pork chops
directions: Dip each pork chop in salad dressing and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place in baking pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: english pea salad
directions: Beginning with the english peas, place a layer in the bottom on a Pyrex dish.
Add a layer of green pepper, a layer of onion, a layer of bacon bits, a layer of cheese.
Spread a layer of mayonnaise over the top.
Chill and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and roll in cinnamon and sugar that have been mixed together.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Layer biscuits into pan. Melt margarine and add brown sugar and water.
Mix. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Invert onto plate while warm.

title: beef stroganoff(mrs. johm f. kennedy)
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Sprinkle freely with salt and pepper; let stand 2 hours in cool place.
Make a roux by blending flour with butter over gentle heat, until mixture bubbles and is smooth.
Gradually stir in beef stock and cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Boil for 2 minutes, then strain into a saucepan.
Add heavy cream and tomato juice, stirring constantly. Simmer very gently, without boiling.

title: pink cherry salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip; chill for 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to chilled milk.
Chill overnight.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips on low heat.
Add cereal and stir.
Take powdered sugar and empty into a large paper bag. Add mixture and shake until coated.

title: dill pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 15 minutes in boiling water.
Drain; pack cucumbers in jars.
To each jar add 1/2 cup vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon powdered alum and 1 tablespoon picking salt.
Add dill and garlic as desired.
Fill with boiling water; seal.
Place in sink of hot water.
Leave until water is cooled.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on a nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: the best beef stew
directions: In a large cooking pot, pour oil, and brown meat and onion together over medium heat.
Hint:
If you'll lightly scorch meat it will enhance the flavor of the broth.
Sprinkle on the flour and stir until meat is coated.
Add 3 quarts of water, add salt, & bay leaf, cover and cook over medium heat at least 4 hours or until meat is good and tender. 2. Prepare carrots and potatoes, then add to pot.
Add corn and green beans and a little more salt as the veggies will absorb a lot.
Add garlic & pepper.
Cover and cook for 30-40 minutes. 3. Add tomatoes, zucchini & noodles.
Then, in a cup, pour gravy mix, add a little water, just enough to thoroughly moisten & not clump, slowly add a little more, until cup is half full.
While stirring stew, add the gravy mixture.
Let it cook for five minutes.

title: chicken taco
directions: Cut chicken into parts and bake, covered, 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Grate cheese, chop onion and tear taco shells into small pieces.
Combine 1 can of soup with 3 Ro-Tel tomatoes plus a little Ro-Tel tomato juice.
Heat this mixture; also, a little chicken broth may be used if needed or desired.
Layer in a greased casserole dish, alternating chicken, onions, tacos and cheese and soup.
Save some taco bits for the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Bring vinegar mixture to a rolling boil; add sugar.
Pour hot mixture over squash.
Bring entire mixture to a boil again and then pack in jars and seal.

title: norwegian waffles
directions: Beat the eggs until light and fluffy. Add 1/2 of the half and half and all the dry ingredients.
Beat the batter until smooth. Add the rest of the half and half, in 1/2 cup portions, until batter is a good consistency.
Stir in the melted butter and bake.

title: danish puff
directions: Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture.
Mix. Shape into ball.
Divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into strips, 12 x 3-inch. Strips should be about 3 inches apart.

title: marinated steak or short ribs
directions: Rub meat on both sides with brown sugar.
Mix soy sauce, vinegar and wine.
Marinate overnight or for a few hours; cook on grill.
Sprinkle with garlic powder before cooking.
If ribs, put bone side down first.

title: sour cream and cucumbers
directions: Peel, then slice cucumbers very thin.
Slice onion very thin and add to cucumbers.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake, uncovered, for 5 to 6 hours at 350°.

title: three bean salad(this dish needs to be fixed the day before you serve it.)
directions: The day before you serve this dish you drain the beans, then place them in a large mixing bowl.
Add green peppers, onions and pimentos.
In a separate bowl, mix the oil and vinegar with sugar, salt and pepper, then pour over the bean mixture.
Toss gently, cover and refrigerate until served.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, place chicken, water and bouillon cubes, parsley, onions, bay leaf, salt and thyme.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, until chicken is tender. Strain broth and return to saucepan.
Remove chicken from bones. Cut into cubes and set aside.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package instructions; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine mushroom soup, milk, water chestnuts, tarragon or basil and salt and pepper.
Mix well and stir in beans.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with onions.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until bubbly and onions are crispy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious onion soup
directions: Before slicing onions, put all bouillon cubes in 2 quarts of hot water and let sit; stir occasionally to encourage cubes to dissolve.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Cook ingredients together for 1 minute.
(Let come to a boil before timing.)
Remove from burner.
Strain to make clear jelly and allow to set 10 minutes (mash as you strain).
Add 1 (6 ounce) bottle Certo and add red or green food coloring.
Stir and pour up quickly before it gels.
Seal in jars (you can use household wax on top after cools and then put lids on after wax sets).

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat. Make paste
of coloring, cocoa, vanilla, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix vinegar and soda together.
Add to just blended in.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) round pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool and split layers.
Frost with Waldorf Frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add cooked squash with remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle croutons on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Put cornstarch in apple cider.
Cook over medium heat.
Add butter and raisins.
When mixture thickens, remove from heat. Ideal over ham.

title: german pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the oleo in a 9-inch pie plate. While butter is melting, slightly mix the eggs, milk and white flour.
By this time, the oleo has melted.
Swirl it around pie plate and egg mixture.
Place in hot oven for 20 minutes.
Serve as pancake with syrup or with just salt (as fried egg) or with cream cheese.

title: calico dip
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and coat with Zesty Italian dressing.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, bell pepper and onion.
Add uncooked rice, water and soups.
Mix well.
Put in covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Pour half of the batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; melt margarine and cream sugar.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Add milk; stir well and add add coconut.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: In blender, blend all ingredients together.
Refrigerate immediately.
This will keep up to 30 days.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: lime cooler
directions: Combine milk, ice cream and juice.
Blend well in mixer or blender.
Serve with extra scoop of ice cream.
Yields 4 cups.

title: steve's hamburgers in mushroom gravy
directions: Form hamburger into patties.
Brown both sides in frypan. Drain off excess fat.
Stir soup to make it smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring to prevent lumps.
Add mushrooms, if you like. Pour soup mixture over hamburgers and turn down heat to low. Cover pan and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad(congealed)
directions: Chill 1/2 of fruit mixture, then cover with sour cream.
Add remaining fruit and chill.

title: custard filled cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch square pan or baking dish about 2-inches deep.
Put buttered dish or pan in oven and let it get hot while mixing batter.
Put eggs in bowl and add melted butter.
Beat until well blended.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vinegar; beat well.
Sift into bowl the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix just until batter is smooth and no lumps appear.
Pour batter into heated dish, then pour cream into the center of batter; don't stir!.
Bake 1 hour until lightly browned.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set them aside.
Mix pudding and milk and set them aside.
Now, mix all other ingredients and add the pudding mix.
Then put a layer of cookies, then a layer of mixture.

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Mix with pimentos, pepper and onion. Dissolve sugar in oil and vinegar and pour over other ingredients. Let marinate overnight.

title: hot wings
directions: Fry frozen wings in 1 stick butter and oil.
Fry until crisp. Drain.
Set aside.
Fry remaining wings.
In saucepan, melt 1 stick butter and 1/2 to 3/4 cup hot sauce; add Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until hot.
Coat wings.

title: my mother's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and eggs in a bowl; mix with electric mixer. Mix in flour, a little at a time, until all flour is mixed.
Add vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°, then turn oven to 350°; bake for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, margarine and salt.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Pour mixture over beaten eggs (slowly), stirring constantly.
Allow to cool and add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not preheat oven!

title: frosty melon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Peel melon, leaving it whole.
Cut a slice at one end, scoop out seeds; drain well.
Place melon upright in bowl.
Add fruit to jello and fill melon cavity.
Fasten cut end or with toothpicks.
Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Spread over entire melon.
Chill.
Cut in horizontal slices to serve.

title: el paso pilaf
directions: Cook onion in oil in large saucepan over medium heat about 5 minutes, until tender, but not brown.
Add beans, broth or water, rice, corn, salsa, lentils, red pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice and lentils are tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Serve over tomato slices.
(Tomato slices may be omitted, good with or without.)
Good meatless dish.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar and 2 cups water for 4 minutes. Dissolve coffee in the other 2 cups heated water. Add to boiling sugar water. Cool. Add liquor and pour into gallon jug with split vanilla bean.
Let set 30 days.
Shake daily.

title: campfire ragout
directions: Layer bottom of pot with bacon.
Add layer of round steak; salt and pepper.
Add layer of onions and layer of sliced carrots; salt and pepper.
Add layer of sliced potatoes; salt and pepper. Add water; cover and cook slowly for about 1 hour on stove, longer on campfire.
To serve, do not stir.
Cut through the layers and dish up.

title: chocolate chip kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and beat until dissolved.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven (350°).
Shut door and turn off heat.
Leave 3 hours or overnight.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: green onion potato casserole
directions: Peel, quarter and boil potatoes until barely tender.
Drain, cool and slice.
Place in a large bowl.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Can add different fruits for taste. Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: selma johnsons hard tack
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time in a large bowl.
Let stand a while, then take small portions and roll out real thin, using graham flour.
Use hard tack rolling pin (after rolling with regular rolling pin) to make marks.
Cut in squares.
Bake at 400°.
I use pizza cutter.

title: tangy ham roll-ups
directions: Mix dill with cream cheese.
Spread mixture on ham slices. Place olives in the center of each ham slice.
Roll and chill for about 1 hour.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Serve chilled.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Combine rice, tomato sauce, stuffed olives, seasonings, cooked meat and broth.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place biscuits on top of casserole dish.
Return to oven and bake at 400° until biscuits are done, about 10 minutes.

title: egg supreme
directions: In 13 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish, spread layer of mushroom soup, layer of eggs, layer of 1/2 bacon, balance of soup, balance of bacon and balance of buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cubes are brown.

title: curry beans
directions: Cook beans as directed.
Meanwhile, melt butter in top of double boiler.
Stir in garlic and curry powder.
Add mayonnaise. Stir often and keep over hot water until time to serve.
Mix "hot" green beans and serve immediately.

title: yummy vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers. Especially good with broccoli florets.
Easy, too!!

title: quick parmesan chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and oregano.
Coat chicken breasts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grammas cracklin cornbread hoecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Soak cracklins in about 1/2 cup of water for about 10 minutes.
Add the corn meal, salt and enough water to make a very thin batter.

Pour into a greased 8-inch or 9-inch cake pan and bake for about 5 minutes and then turn oven down to 400° and bake another 15 to 20 minutes (ovens and tastes vary, we like ours real brown and crunchy).

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix with mixer at least 15 minutes, the other 2 sticks of butter, the eggs, the sugar and the vanilla flavoring.
Pour this mixture over the crumb crust.
Slice the bananas and place on top.
Put the pineapple on top of the bananas. Drain first and use the juice to brush on the bananas and pineapple to keep them from turning brown.
Put Cool Whip on top of fruit. Sprinkle this with nuts and add cherries.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut breads into rounds and butter one side.
Mix the first 4 ingredients together; spread on unbuttered side of bread.
Dip bread into the Parmesan cheese.
(May be frozen at this stage.) Place on cookie sheet and broil (cheese side up) until golden. Makes approximately 10 dozen.

title: pampered chef-quick apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: peanut delight
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted butter in mixing bowl; mix well.
Spread evenly in buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Using fingers, pat mixture evenly and firmly.	Spread ice cream over top.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Spread Cool Whip over peanuts.
Cover and freeze. To serve, cut in squares.
Drizzle a small amount of syrup over top.

title: remade pickles
directions: Boil together all ingredients except pickles for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add pickles to hot mixture.
Return to jar and let stand 2 weeks in refrigerator.
When pickles are gone, drain a can of sliced beets and put into jar.
This makes very good pickled beets.

title: chicken and rice gumbo
directions: Rinse meat in cold water.

Pat dry and beat with meat mallet on both sides. Soak for 20 to 30 minutes in Dales sauce seasoning. Drop into hot grease and brown on both sides. Remove from grease and make gravy. Delicious served over mashed potatoes or rice. (You may also use round steak.)

title: amish slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Cool in refrigerator. Slaw can be frozen and served later.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat the sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, 1/2 the butter, milk, nutmeg and cinnamon well.
Place into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mix the rest of the ingredients for the topping.
Sprinkle on top of casserole; bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice room temperature tomato into 4 slices.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Coat both sides of tomato slices with dry mixture. Fry golden brown in oil.
Serve immediately.
Serves two.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Cook chicken, remove from bones and cut into chunks.
Combine chicken, enchilada sauce, soup, onion, garlic salt and pepper. Place half of corn chips in a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer with chicken mixture, then remaining corn chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour chicken broth over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry or crust.
Mix 1 1/3 cups flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cut in 1/2 cup of shortening with a pastry blender until mixture looks like tiny peas. Sprinkle in 3 to 4 tablespoons cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring with a fork after each addition.
Mix lightly until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl (add 1 to 2 teaspoons of water if necessary).
Pat in bottom and up sides of quiche dish, 8 x 2-inches or round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: no cooking lemon cheese cake pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip until fluffy. Add pie filling and gradually beat with mixer. Pile into pie crust.
Refrigerate two hours.

title: noodle soup parmigiana
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients, except cheese; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
To serve, spoon into bowls; sprinkle with cheeses.
Makes about 5 (1-cup) servings.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Then add applesauce.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture with oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until dark.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle bottom with seasoned herb stuffing.
Mix first 5 ingredients well and salt to taste.
Pour into dish.
Top with more herb stuffing.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts in lemon sauce
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions omitting salt.
Drain.
Place Brussels sprouts in a shallow 2-quart casserole and keep warm.
Melt margarine in a saucepan; add mayonnaise, lemon juice and celery salt.
Beat with a wire whisk until smooth; cook over medium heat until hot, stirring constantly (do not boil).
Pour sauce over sprouts; sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Cake:
Mix together flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, and salt.
In another bowl, mix butter on high for 30 seconds.
Add sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat on medium. Gradually add flour; mix until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press center of each with thumb.
Drain cherries (reserve juice).
Press halved cherry into center of each ball.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Steam vegetables together until done but not mushy.
Melt butter and Velveeta cheese together.
Pour over vegetables. Crumble crackers and spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: fudge
directions: Heat sugar, milk and butter.
When dissolved, stir in marshmallows.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; remove from heat and add all 3 types of chocolate.
Stir to melt and blend well. Pour in well buttered dish and refrigerate.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: "oh boy" waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; beat only until moistened (batter will be thin).
Bake in preheated baker. Makes 10 to 12.

title: crunchy chinese cole slaw
directions: Break up uncooked noodles.
Combine with all ingredients and cabbage.
Toss together.
Add dressing.
Toss well and chill.

title: mock pierogi
directions: Peel potatoes and onions and cube.
Boil potatoes; add salt. Melt oleo; add onions and saute.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Mix potatoes into sauteed onions and let simmer for 10 minutes or more.
Cook macaroni; mix altogether and enjoy.
Save some of the potato water to add to mixture if too dry.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 2 rolls about as round as a cracker.
Wrap tightly in foil; refrigerate for 24 hours. Take out, unwrap and place on a rack.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn meat over when half done.

title: hot bacon salad dressing
directions: Heat water to simmer.
Beat egg and add to water.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add to the sauce.
Simmer until it thickens.
(Simmering is very important.)

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain cooked noodles; run cold water over them 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients; add to noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain pork sausage.
Cook and drain lima beans. Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in oven dish and melt.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all other ingredients except peaches.
After butter has melted, pour in mixed ingredients, then add peaches on top of that. Bake for approximately 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Melt butter.
Add carrots and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add flour, broth and milk.
Cook/simmer till thick.
Add cheese and rest of ingredients. Heat till thoroughly warm.
Do not boil.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt margarine in pan with cocoa.
Remove from heat and beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth pancakes
directions: Mix corn meal, sugar, flour and soda. Add buttermilk, egg yolks, melted margarine and vanilla. Mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1 Tbsp. sugar and beat again until stiff peak forms. Fold egg whites into the batter. Have skillet heated and cook pancakes until done.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add nuts and lemon rind.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pierce in several places with small skewer.

title: add to cake mix
directions: Add this to a store bought cake mix to make it taste homemade. Mix cake like it says then add these ingredients.
If cake mix has oil, leave out the shortening.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions, minus butter (cool).
Add chopped green onions and green pepper and sliced olives.
Drain artichokes.
Mix a little of the marinade with the mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour over rice and artichokes and toss gently.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken dry and then dip into liquid butter which garlic (mashed) has been added, then dip into bread crumb mix of crumbs, parsley flakes, and Parmesan cheese.
Place chicken into greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Check to see if browning. Take off cover and brown.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix and shape into ball.
Garnish with shredded cheese, bacon bits, olives or whatever.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 3 minutes; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft. Add flour and seasonings and mix well. Pinch off small amounts, work into thin circle and press around olive. Bake on greased sheet at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: chicken with dressing dumplings
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour and paprika and heat in margarine.
Add salt, pepper and water and heat until thickened. Put in large casserole dish.
Mix soup and 1 3/4 cups water and bring to boil.
Add to meat mixture in casserole and stir.
Add onions and mix.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all in one pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In large container, combine all ingredients.
Store tightly covered.
For each serving, mix 1/4 cup mix with 1 cup boiling water.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: bina's fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift 2 cups flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Save 1 cup flour to dredge fruits before adding to mixture.
Add flour with peach juice to shortening mixture.
Add flavoring, fruits and nuts.
Line tube pan with brown paper.
Grease pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours. Cover top of pan with greased brown paper.
This prevents cake from browning too quickly on top.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate drops and peanut butter in microwave.
Remove and add nuts.
Work quickly. Pour in lightly greased dish.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: paradise salad
directions: Mix and let chill.

title: festive cranberry tea
directions: Boil cranberries with 1 quart water until berries pop. Strain.
Save juice and boil together with 3 quarts water, sugar, cinnamon candies and cloves.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Serve hot.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and let stand.
Cream sugar, egg, shortening and vanilla.
Fold in flour.
Add date mixture. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with snacks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: penne with tomatoes, olives and two cheeses
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in heavy Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and onion; saute until translucent.
Mix in tomatoes, dried basil and red pepper.
Bring to boil, breaking up tomatoes with fork.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer until mixture thickens, about 1 1/4 hours and is reduced to 6 cups.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Sprinkle crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Take chilled milk and whip until foamy.
Add lemon juice and sugar. Whip 3 to 5 more minutes.
Pour into dish with crumbs.
Top with more crumbs.
Put in freezer until hard (3 to 5 hours).
Store in freezer.

title: shrimp cocktail hors d'oeuvres
directions: Place cream cheese on plate.
Mix tomato catsup and enough horseradish to your taste, mild, tangy or hot.
Drain, then rinse the shrimp well under cold water.
Drain again. Dump shrimp over cream cheese and dump sauce over both. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: For chicken broth, use broth from chicken combine all ingredients above in greased casserole dish.
Add topping and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chris' meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in a large loaf pan or can be put in 2 small loaf pans.
Spread ketchup on top
and bake.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart baking dish.
In a medium saucepan, cover scallops with cold water; bring to a boil and drain as soon as water boils.
Do not overcook.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter and mix with the breadcrumbs.
Set aside.
Cut green pepper, onion and celery into chunks and saute in the remaining butter about 5 minutes.
Layer scallops, vegetables and crumbs in the baking dish, making 2 layers of each, ending with crumbs.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Pour the cream over the top and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple whip(romania)
directions: Wash and quarter the apples, remove seeds and boil until soft. Drain apples into another pot and sieve the apples (make a puree). The the drained apple liquid add gelatine, dissolve it, add sugar and return back to heat until it boils. Remove from heat. After the liquid has cooled, pour in a bowl, add the apple puree and whip until foamy. Pour into serving cups and serve. Other fruits may be used in the same manner.

title: peter pan chocolate surprises
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add gradually into creamed mixture until well blended.
Chill dough at least 30 minutes.
Wrap about 1 level teaspoon of dough around each chocolate piece.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar and let cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef and onions in large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in cooked macaroni, tomato sauce, corn, chili powder and seasoned salt.
Simmer on stove top at medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and serve immediately.

title: easy veggie salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the beans, cucumber, carrots, green pepper and radishes. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, mix well. Pour over vegetables and toss to coat. Serve with slotted spoon. Refrigerate left overs up to 2 days.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Drain green beans, reserving 1/2 c. juice.
Brown ground beef with onion in skillet stirring until crumbly.
Place potatoes in greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spoon ground beef mixture over potatoes.
Combine beans and garlic salt in bowl, and spoon over ground beef mixture.
Combine soup and 1/2 c. bean juice in a bowl and spread over beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Make Jell-O, using the pineapple juice, adding enough water to make 2 cups cold water. Let firm.
Mix in cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Add nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with topping and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: May substitute lemon supreme cake mix and omit flour, sugar and baking powder; use 4 eggs.

title: cold vegetable platter salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients for dressing and set aside.
Combine mushrooms, green beans, onion, artichokes, hearts of palm in large bowl.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss and chill overnight.

title: ratatouille
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat olive oil until hot, but not smoking. Saute onions and garlic first for several minutes.
Add zucchini and green peppers; continue to cook, stirring.
Add eggplant and tomatoes.
Saute, stirring for several minutes.
Season with salt. Add thyme and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Place in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes, stirring once in awhile to prevent sticking.
Do not add liquid.
Do not cover.
It is important to stir occasionally.
When finished, mixture looks like a stew. Sprinkle top with a little chopped parsley before serving.

title: grated sweet potato-pudding
directions: Combine sugars, butter, spices and salt.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Stir in grated sweet potato; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until pudding is browned and the potato is done.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and dice mushrooms.
Place in pot with water. Add bouillon cubes, butter and onion.
Cook gently until mushrooms and onions are done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well until oil disappears. Sift all dry ingredients and mix well with egg mixture.
Fold in grated zucchini; add nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan, 3/4 full.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cheese well.
Stir in chopped artichoke hearts and place in a 2-cup casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven until slightly browned and bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers, rye rounds or Melba toast.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: lazy cook's escalloped hamburg
directions: Brown hamburg in electric frypan; drain.
Add large can of stewed tomatoes or 2 standard size cans (the kind that has peppers, onions, etc.); mix well.
Cook at low heat.
While cooking, prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and add to hamburg tomato mixture.
Cover and simmer at low heat, stirring occasionally.
(Can also freeze some to serve later.)

title: beer bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quik creamy fruit dip
directions: Microwave on High the cream cheese in uncovered, small, microwave-safe dish for 30 to 45 seconds or until softened.
Stir until creamy.
Gradually blend yogurt into cream cheese.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Refrigerate until served.
Serve with sliced apples, kiwi fruit, pears or grapes.
Makes about 3/4 cup. Contains 30 calories per tablespoon.

title: hot wassail
directions: Heat and serve hot.
Good winter day beverage.

title: working person's roast
directions: You will need a large cooking bag.
Place the roast in the cooking bag.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over roast.
Pour the Worcestershire sauce over the soup.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over this.
Add seasonings.
Seal bag.
Place in cake pan and put in oven at 250° from 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.
Your roast will be tender and the gravy is already made.

title: pumpkin corn bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
in a large bowl.	Beat until well blended.
Pour
into
a greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf or 12 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in 2 quarts water with 1/2 cup salt overnight.
Drain and wash off, then add seasons and heat.
Do not boil.
Seal in jars tightly.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Spread a layer of stew meat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup and add other soups and Worcestershire sauce. Add layer of vegetables and pour water over.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 5 hours and don't peek.
This is the secret. Good with biscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cream coleslaw
directions: Crisp cabbage in cold water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients except paprika and blend well.
Pour over cabbage and stir to coat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Boil eggs and chop.
Make pastry for any size dish you plan to use.
Put pastry in dish and then the chopped chicken, chopped eggs and salt and pepper.
Pour thickened chicken broth over all this.
Make sure it is very juicy.
Put a top crust on; brown crust and it's done.
This is the best and easiest chicken pie you will ever eat.
Of course, you can add any vegetables you like.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Cut candy bars into 1/4-inch pieces and place in the pastry shell;
set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, sour cream and peanut butter;
beat on low speed just until combined.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 35-40 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
In a small heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips with cream over low heat until smooth.
Spread over filling.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Cut with a warm knife.
Yield:
8-10 servings.

title: flan
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender; set aside.
Cook water and sugar in saucepan on high, mixing constantly until it turns caramelized and light brown.
Pour caramelized sugar in bottom of a baking dish.
Pour mixture from blender on top and bake in casserole placed in baking pan of hot water.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer corn
directions: Combine corn, sugar, salt and water; boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oleo and milk.
Cool and place in freezer cartons.

title: chocolate surprise cupcakes(makes 60 cupcakes)
directions: Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Set mixture aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Mix nuts and sugar together in small dish.
Fill cupcake tin 1/2 full of cake batter.
Add 1 tablespoon cheese mixture to each cupcake.
Sprinkle with nut/sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham and cheese chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a Dutch oven, bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add ham and remaining ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: one pan ham and cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 8 x 8 x 2 baking dish. Mix baking mix, milk, salt, mustard, parsley, pepper and eggs with a fork until batter is a uniform color. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake, uncovered, until knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 45 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers and melted butter together. Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together next 4 ingredients and beat 15 minutes.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas on top.
Top bananas with pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple
and
sprinkle
with
crushed
mixed
nuts and cherries. Chill and serve.

title: dilly dip(chip or vegetable)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: hot sauce
directions: Fill pan (kettle) with tomatoes; add remaining ingredients. Boil together on low heat about 2 to 3 hours.
Pour into sterile jars.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pea salad(serves 6)
directions: Layer with small pieces of lettuce and 1/2 of ingredients (make 2 layers), ending with lettuce on top.

title: easy pumpkin swirl
directions: Filling recipe follows; heat oven to 375°, grease a 15x10x1 jelly roll pan. Line top and sides with wax paper.

Grease wax paper. Beat eggs and sugar unitl fluffy, beat in pumpkin, stir in dry ingredients. Pour into pan, spread evenly sprinkle with nuts. Bake for 13-15 min. Invert onto towel dusted with powdered sugar, peel off wax paper, roll up cake and towel together from short side.
Place seem side down on wire rack, cool completely. Unroll cake, spread with filling, re-roll cake, refrigerate untilready to serve.

title: italian cheese omelet
directions: Break eggs into medium bowl. Beat with rotary beater until mixed but not foamy.
Add salt, parsley, cheese and pepper.

title: "phil's cheesecake"
directions: Cream the cream cheese in bowl.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch and flour.
Add butter; beat.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Leave in oven 2 hours with door open.
Top with fruit topping.
Cake usually cracks in middle.

title: joann's lemon delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Work flour and margarine together like for pie crust.
Add nuts if desired.
Press into an 11 1/2 x 7-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheddar apple breakfast lasagna
directions: In small bowl blend sour cream and brown sugar.
Chill.
Place 6 French toast slices in bottom of greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Layer ham, 2 c. of cheese and remaining 6 slices of french toast. Spread apple filling over top, sprinkle with granola.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining 1/2 c. cheddar cheese and bake about 5 minutes more until cheese is melted and casserole is hot.
Serve with sour cream mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and stir ingredients on low heat until done.
Mixture will ball up.
Store in Ziploc bag until used.
Good for young and old, nontoxic.

title: scrumptuous bars
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and margarine.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares and store in airtight container.

title: grated chicken and scampi
directions: Boil chicken in water until fully cooked, cut up into pieces, then in saucepan, brown chicken on both sides in margarine; drain. Add onion, tomato sauce, cheese, parsley and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Stir in shrimp and wine; heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in flour first and last, alternately with milk.
Add extracts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door until then.
Check to see if cake leaves sides of pan.
Bake in a tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Have ingredients at room temperature.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Bake in two loaf pans (greased) for 50 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix and cook the first 7 ingredients.
Discard bay leaf.
Add cottage cheese and spinach.
Boil lasagne noodles for about 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix on high in mixer for about 5 minutes.
Also can be mixed in blender.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pudding mix.
Cook remaining ingredients until blended and pour over rolls.
Cover tight with aluminum foil and leave setting at room temperature overnight.
In the morning, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Leave set for a few minutes and carefully turn over on a plate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender. Drain. Mix with other ingredients. Save approximately 1/2 cup stuffing mix for topping. Mix well and place in a greased casserole dish. Top with reserved stuffing mix. Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and vegetable soup
directions: In a large skillet saute butter, onions and celery until tender.
Add flour to mixture, turn heat to low, and cook for about 45 minutes, stirring constantly, until flour mixture is golden in color.
Add chicken stock and next 4 ingredients.
Turn heat to medium; add cooked chicken and vegetables and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve immediately.

title: mom's secret recipe for delmonico potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender; let cool.
Peel off skins and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Melt butter.
Add flour and slowly stir in milk.
Cook until thick.
Add in cheese and stir until melted. (Can add onion, if desired.)

title: easy frozen corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat, cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate overnight. Freeze in morning.

title: mayhaw jelly
directions: Pick and wash mayhaws.
Put in a pot and cover the mayhaws with water and cook until tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour into jelly bag (flour sack bag, etc.) and squeeze.
Mayhaws may be cooked a second time, but combine your first cooking juice with the second cooking juice, if you do cook a second time.
Mix juice and Sure-Jell and a few drops of red food coloring and 1 teaspoon butter in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a full boil. Add sugar and return to hard boil and boil for 3 minutes (takes continual stirring).
Let stand for about a minute (can sterilize jars during that minute).
Skim and pour in sterilized jars and seal. Makes 7 (1/2) pints.

title: apple skillet coffee cake
directions: Melt in 8 or 9-inch iron skillet 1/4 stick margarine. Add apples. Cook until fork-tender. Stir in brown sugar; set aside. Mix flour, melted 1/2 cup margarine, white sugar, egg, vanilla and milk. Mix and pour over apples in skillet. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Salt chicken.
Mix soup with rice and pour in baking dish. Place chicken on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken and rice are done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour pudding (dry powder) into pineapple in large bowl and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate and serve after chilled for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and mix well. Add egg and mix. Add flour, vanilla, and enough buttermilk to mix very well. Batter will be stiff. Put peaches in baking dish and spread batter over peaches. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Add 1/2 cup milk to the cake mix and 1 stick softened oleo. Bake 1/2 of the cake batter 20 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt the caramels with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour on top of cake mix, then spread the bag of chocolate chips on top of caramel. Spread pecans over that.
Pour the remaining cake batter over the top.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla together.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Stir in small amount of flour and soda beaten until well mixed.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add margarine and cheese; mix well.
Shape into balls a little smaller than a pecan.
Press a little.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly tan in color.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Saute onion and celery in cooking oil.
When tender add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Serve on rolls or on the side.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Crumble bread.
Add eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix into batter.
Put half of batter in bottom of unbaked pie crust. Spread chopped rhubarb on top and add remaining batter.
Put lattice crust over the top or make a lot of holes in top crust.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, crumbs, celery, onion, cheese and salt.
Add beaten eggs and stir in milk and butter.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with parsley and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crab imperial
directions: Chop red and green peppers fine; saute for 1 minute in butter. Cool.
Add dry mustard, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and salt; mix well.
Fold in crab meat.
Turn out into crab shell baking dishes.
Spread small amount of mayonnaise on top.
Brown in moderate oven.
Makes 6 moderate servings.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pan.

title: baker's clay
directions: Rocks are made of different minerals.
A mineral is any useful substance that occurs naturally in the earth's crust.
Most minerals grow in special shapes called crystals.
They grow larger by adding more layers of the same shape.
To grow some crystals of your own, do the following:

title: cranberry torte
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder. Add dates, cranberries, pecans, eggs, buttermilk and oil. Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into shells.
Chill for 2 hours.
Top with cherries.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk. Add broccoli. Stir slowly until thawed. Add uncooked rice and grated cheese.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: good squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain.
Add all ingredients together and top with melter butter and crackers.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and cover with approximately 25 crushed Ritz crackers. Top with 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Add 6 cups water and then combine 1 cup flour and 1 cup water. Add to mixture and simmer 2 hours, stirring often or it will stick.

title: diet spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon sugar, tomatoes, pepperoni, onions, olives and bell pepper.
Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Bring 4 cups of water to rapid boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 cup oil.
Add lasagna and cook, uncovered, for approximately 20 minutes.
Drain lasagna and rinse in cold water.

title: cheeese cake
directions: Mix crackers and butter together and spread in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix Jell-O and boiling water and let cool.
Mix cream cheese thoroughly with a fork.
Whip milk and fold into the Jell-O with the cheese and pour over crust.
Sprinkle 6 or 7 graham crackers on top of cheesecake and refrigerate overnight.

title: basic cut-out cookie dough
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Chill overnight. Roll out thin on a floured surface.
Use cookie cutters of the season.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
When cool, decorate and frost.

title: hot bean and potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and keep warm.
In large saucepan, fry bacon; crumble and set aside. Add onions, celery and parsley to bacon drippings and cook until soft.
Add reserved bean sauce, seasonings and vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir in beans; heat through.
Add hot potatoes and crumbled bacon, tossing lightly to coat.
Serve at once.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: spinach-pea salad
directions: Thaw and drain peas and spinach.
Layer in bowl the spinach, onion, green pepper, peas, cheese and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise.
Refrigerate 8 hours; mix well.
Fry or microwave 1 pound bacon; crumble and mix into salad.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: oatmeal bread*
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk and cold water, heat.
Pour hot liquid over butter, sugar and salt, stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour, dissolved yeast and oats.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic; shape in ball.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat surface of dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place about 1 hour or until double.
Punch down, cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape to form 2 loaves (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches). Cover and let rise 45 minutes or to double.
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Butter tops when done.

title: instant tea for a crowd
directions: Dissolve tea and sugar in hot water.
Add remaining water. Stir.
Makes 20 gallons.

title: keep skinny carrot cake(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch fluted tube pan with nonstick spray.
In large bowl, using mixer, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Using mixer on low speed, beat in milk powder, flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Pour batter into pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes. Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Spread batter in greased jelly-roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inches).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 4 dozen bars.

title: apricot muffin kuchen
directions: Soften butter; blend in honey and sugar. Add pecans and preheat oven to 350°. Halve sourdough muffins. Place split side up on cookie sheet and bake 5 minutes. Place about 3 apricots on each muffin half and spoon on topping mixture.
Bake 5 minutes or until lightly brown. Serves 6.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichoke hearts with fork; mix with other ingredients in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until bubbly). Put under broiler to brown.
Serve with flatbreads, pita chips, bagel chips or crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until smooth.
Add oleo, vanilla, flour, sugar, cocoa, and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees until done (it won't shake).
Top with meringue.
Bake until meringue is light brown.

title: cheese corn muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cornmeal; stir in	cheese.
Add
egg,
milk and shortening; stir just to moisten dry
ingredients.
Fill greased 2-inch muffin cups 2/3 full; bake at	400° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in bread cubes.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Slightly mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Combine olive oil, juice, vinegar and salt.
Crush the instant onion with mortar and pestle or back of wooden spoon; blend with ginger or cumin.
Add to the juice mixture.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, milk, flour and vanilla together and pour over oleo.
Top with fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: orange bran loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 6 mini loaf pans and one 6 x 3 x 2-inch foil loaf pans.

title: cheese fingers
directions: Slice bread crosswise into 1-inch fingers, leaving attached. Mix cream cheese and dressing mix together.
Spread on bread. Pile on toppings.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown. Store in airtight container.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into serving dish and chill.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix ground beef, onion, pepper, chili mix and tomato sauce together.
Pour into pie crust.
Layer with cheese.
Cover with the second crust.
Put into oven at 350° until browned.

title: low-fat fudge
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Take off eye and add last 4 ingredients.
Stir until mixed good together.
Let cool.
Pour into a buttered glass dish.

title: tiramisu
directions: Cut across the middle of the sponge cake to form 2 discs about 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick each.
Blend the coffee and liqueur together.
Sprinkle the bottom half of the cake with the coffee liqueur blend, enough to flavor it strongly, but don't saturate the cake so much that it will collapse.

title: pickled beets(this was sister mallery's recipe)
directions: Bring to a boil the lemon juice, honey and water; pour over cooked beets in jars.
Process 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix all together and roll in ball or in a heart mold.
Top with crushed pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with cherries.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: sauteed shrimp and mushrooms
directions: In frypan, cook garlic until light brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, or until shrimp are firm and pink.
Serve over rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: crust
directions: Use a skillet.
Saute coconut in butter until golden.
Press all but 2 tablespoons into the bottom and up the sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Put the 2 tablespoons on top of pie.

title: chicken divan
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Shred chicken and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix can of soup and 1/2 can of milk together and pour over chicken.
Fix stuffing by directions and spoon over chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle broccoli over stuffing and place cheese slices over broccoli.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Place single layer of chicken breasts in baking pan or pans. Mix 1 bouillon cube in 1/4 cup hot water and pour over each 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° until pink is gone.
Do not overbake. Cool and cut chicken into 3/4-inch cubes.
Leave walnuts in larger pieces.
Toast in oven until brown.
Serve for garnishment.

title: hershey's chocolatetown bundt cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Stir in Hershey's mini chips.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Glaze with Satiny Mini Chip Glaze.

title: no-sugar-added lemon cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Let cool to room temperature. In a blender, combine the cooled gelatin mixture, cream cheese and cottage cheese. Cover and process until smooth. Transfer to a bowl and fold in whipped topping. Pour in prepared crust. Sprinkle on crumbs. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Garnish with reduced-sugar cherry pie topping.

title: pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve jello with juice of pineapple and enough hot water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Put in refrigerator while mixing cream cheese, pineapple, nuts and celery.
Then add the cooled jello (slightly jelled) and mix ingredients.
Next, fold in the whipped cream.
Pour into the mold and chill until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients and stir (do not use an electric mixer).
The zucchini gives moisture to the batter but it will still be on the soft side.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 3 (4 x 8-inch) loaves.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Add sugar to warm water and stir.
Add yeast and let stand 5 minutes.
Sift flour and salt.
Add yeast mixture and oil to flour.
Knead until a soft smooth ball is formed.
Place on a lightly floured board.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Place in greased baking dish and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Good!!!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and melted margarine.
Press into bottom of Pyrex cake pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust and chill.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add both packages of thawed strawberries and pineapple.
Chill until jello begins to thicken.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger, cracker crumbs, egg, catsup, onion, salt, pepper, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Mold into large patties. Mix mushroom soup, garlic salt and milk.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake in 9 x 13 pan. While cake is baking, mix the milk and sugar; cook, but do not boil. While cake is hot, spoon mixture over cake. Let drizzle through cake. Spread Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle with frozen coconut.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil or steam zucchini	and onion.
Drain water and set aside. Mix soup, sour
cream
and grated carrot and fold into zucchini and onion.	Melt 1/2 cup butter and mix with stuffing mix. Sprinkle 1/2
stuffing
mixture
into
8-inch casserole. Pour zucchini mixture
over.
Sprinkle
remaining stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Beat eggs first. Add dry ingredients. Fold in nuts, cherries, chips and raisins. Bake at 350° in greased loaf pans(s) for 1 hour or 1/2 hour in muffin tins.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and
mold
them into a mound on plate. Pour sauce over mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cook onions in boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 minutes. In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Blend in cream cheese until smooth. Stir in vegetables.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Melt remaining butter and toss with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle crumbs over casserole. Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Makes 10 servings.

title: new potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, do not peel, cut into cubes.
Cook bacon; dice. Mix all together except dill seed.
Add last and a little at a time; it's easy to use too much.
This recipe improves after a few hours in the fridge.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and add any of the following:
can of mushrooms, 1/2 cup almonds, 3 sliced boiled eggs, can of green peas or can of water chestnuts.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cornish hens with toasted rice stuffing
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add rice only and pecans; saute over low heat, stirring occasionally, until rice turns golden brown.
Add seasoning packet, orange juice, water and raisins to rice mixture and stir well.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat and cool.
Remove packet from cavity of hens and discard.
Wash hens inside and out and drain well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fill cavity of each hen with 1/2 to 3/4 cup rice mixture.
Cover and warm remaining rice to serve with hens.
Tie drumsticks together with string and place on rack in a roasting pan.
Brush each hen with melted butter.
Roast in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until juices run clear when hen is pierced.
Baste occasionally with melted butter while roasting.
Remove from oven. Remove and discard string.
Serve hens on a bed of the remaining rice stuffing.
Serves 2.

title: gert's fudge(various flavors)
directions: Heat sugar and milk to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add either peanut butter or morsels.
Pour in buttered pan and cool.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Halve zucchini lengthwise and place in a medium saucepan of boiling water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Drain and let cool on wire racks.
Scoop out pulp, leaving firm shells.
Chop pulp into small pieces.
Place zucchini pulp and remaining ingredients in a bowl. Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Place zucchini shells on a lightly greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon zucchini mixture into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: heavenly spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Cook beef until brown.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream with onion and pepper.
Butter casserole; spread half spaghetti on bottom.
Cover with cheese mixture; add rest of spaghetti and cover with sauce.
Cover.
Keep refrigerated until 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: make ahead and freeze meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Break bread crumbs into large mixing bowl. Stir in milk, eggs and seasonings.
Mix well.
Work in meat until well blended.
Press into 3 oblong lightly greased pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Bake 1 hour.
Each loaf serves 6.
May be frozen for 6 months.

title: sam's stir-fry
directions: Optional:
Peppers, onions, mushrooms, broccoli or cauliflower may be added, all depending on your likeness of vegetables.

title: deer meat stew
directions: Marinate meat overnight in equal parts vinegar and water. Drain and wash meat; cut into small pieces.
Salt and pepper meat; roll in flour.
Brown in skillet.
Place meat in cooker.
Steam until done (1 1/2 hours).
Add vegetables and seasoning.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grape jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and powdered sugar.
When the Jell-O is set and firm, spread cheese mixture on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack washed cucumbers into hot, sterilized jars.
Into each jar, put the following:
powdered alum, hot pepper or crushed hot pepper, dill or dill seed, garlic or crushed garlic and grape leaf.
Bring to a boil the following: vinegar, water and salt. Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and seal by placing jars in boiling water for approximately 2 minutes.
Watch time so pickles will not get too soft.
Yield:
6 to 8 quarts, depending on size of cucumbers.
Small, tiny cucumbers are best.
Check seal carefully for several days.

title: healthy, healthy chicken soup
directions: Place chicken parts, water, celery, salt, pepper and tomatoes in pot.
Fill 2/3 full with water.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat and remove chicken.
Skim off the fat.
Add onion soup mix and cabbage; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Remove bones and skin from chicken; chop into bite-size pieces.
Return to pot and cook uncovered for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.
Contains 240 calories.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts in large mixing bowl and let stand for an hour.
Stir often so that the mixture makes its own juice. Combine dry ingredients and add to apples.
Then add oil, vanilla and eggs.

title: creole chicken casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix rice, broth, pepper sauce, onion and garlic in 3-quart casserole.
Cover; microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in remaining ingredients; break up tomatoes.
Cover tightly; microwave for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes, until hot.

title: prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients at one time.
Beat with electric mixer until eggs are well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, crumble and reserve 1/3 cup bacon fat.
Cook onion in reserved fat until tender.
Blend sugar, flour, salt, paprika, celery seed and black pepper.
Add vinegar and 1 cup of water.
Cook and stir until bubbly and thick.
Add bacon and potatoes.
Toss lightly, making sure all contents are heated thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley and pimento.
Serves 8.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients and toss well.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Add to chicken mixture, stirring well.
Chill several hours before serving.
Serve on lettuce with croissant rolls or put in cheese tart shells.

title: pickle beets
directions: Boil beets until tender. Blanch with cold water; skins will slip off. Make syrup by boiling together water, vinegar, sugar and salt. Add whole cloves. Add a pinch of black pepper. Add beets. Bring to a boil. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Freeze until needed.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Cut cooked chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix soup with milk. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dietetic maple syrup
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Serve hot.
Up to 1 cup may be used as a free item.

title: stroganoff sandwich
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Remove from heat and drain. Add mushrooms, sour cream, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
Mix well.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir lightly, just enough to mix.
Divide batter in three wax paper lined 3 x 7-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer bread cubes, meat and cheese.
Mix beaten egg, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, add mushrooms,
cover and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes. Uncover for last 10 minutes to let top brown.

title: frosty mandarin
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain oranges; reserve liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in sherbet and mandarin oranges.
Pour in 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables, celery and onions.
Drain.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise and water.
Put a little oil in bottom of baking dish; spread Pepperidge Farm dressing in bottom of casserole.
Mix vegetable and soup mixture together.
Spread shredded cheese and more dressing on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy burritos
directions: Cook beef until brown; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in beans and chili.
Spoon equal amount of meat mixture into each tortilla.
Top with grated cheese.
Roll tortilla and place seam down in pan.
Cover with foil and heat in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: rita lee's chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice evenly into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Place the chicken pieces over the raw rice.
Mix the soups and water together thoroughly and pour over the chicken and rice. Cover with foil and bake in a slow oven at 325° for 2 hours.

title: low-calorie, low-fat pineapple dessert
directions: Using a fork, tear the angel food cake into bite-size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex pan.
Spread the pineapple over the top of the angel food cake pieces.
Prepare the Jell-O pudding by the directions and spread pudding over the pineapple. The banana slices are layered over the pudding.
Cover it all with the Cool Whip and chill overnight.
