When ready to serve, cut the dessert into squares.

title: eclair cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Put 1 layer of crackers in bottom of pan. Cover with half of the pudding mix. Add another layer of crackers and the remaining pudding.
Add another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Add topping. Keep refrigerated.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Pat remaining mixture into ungreased oblong cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked, cooled layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake again 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: candy cookies
directions: Combine oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and combine with creamed mixture.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 35 minutes. Take out of oven and cover with miniature marshmallows. Return to oven until marshmallows melt.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat on high speed until fluffy. Stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Since the cake has the soft tunnel of fudge, ordinary doneness tests cannot be used.
Test after 60 minutes by observing a dry, shiny brownie-type crust.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine the melted margarine and the crackers. Spread over the vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken inside and out with salt and pepper.
Stuff with onions and sage.
Lift skin from breast of chicken, taking care not to break the skin, and pour in 2 tablespoons of melted butter mixed with the garlic.
Truss chicken.
Run skin with olive oil.
Sprinkle entire chicken with rosemary leaves and pepper. Halfway through cooking, sprinkle with salt.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat all ingredients, then add shrimp.
Great with raw veggies.

title: *friga salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill before using.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf with vegetable spray.
In a large bowl, flake the salmon, removing bones and skin.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Press into a loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes until golden brown or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes; loosen eggs and lift out of pan onto serving plate.
Cut into slices.

title: cornbread mix with cheese and bacon
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Add egg and 1/4 pound oleo and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, evaporated milk, 1 cup sugar and eggs (add cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and ginger as for pumpkin pie).
Pour into pan and top with topping of cake mix plus 4 tablespoons oleo, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (no need to use mixer) until dough forms a ball.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: pecan squares
directions: Line a long pan or dish (9 x 13-inch) with whole graham crackers.
Melt the butter.
While this is melting, beat the sugar, egg and milk together.
Add this to melted butter and let reach boiling point.
Mix in the nuts, coconut and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour all over layer of graham crackers and top with another layer of whole graham crackers.

title: no-roll pastry
directions: In medium bowl with fork, stir flour with salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

Sprinkle cold water into flour mixture, a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with fork after each addition, until pastry is just moist enough to hold together. Press to bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate.
Flute edge; cover with plastic wrap.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli in 2 quarts water in saucepan for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from heat.
Saute onion in butter in large saucepan until tender.
Add flour; blend well.
Add broccoli and broccoli liquid. Simmer for several minutes.
Stir in milk, bouillon cubes, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer for several minutes longer. Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until tender. Add soup, rice, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Mix together in casserole and bake until tender.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crispy no bake cereal treats
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper. In large bowl, combine all ingredients except coconut.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Place on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 1-2 hours or until firm.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Drink 3 ounces per day.
This cleans out arteries and cells; keeps cholesterol low and cells unclogged.

title: meal in a pan
directions: Line large baking dish with meat.
Arrange other ingredients on top of meat ending up with cabbage leaves to completely cover. Add bacon strips on top of cabbage leaves.
Season as needed to taste.
Cover with foil & bake at 350° for 1 hour-1 hour 15 minutes.
Small ears of corn may also be added.
May place baking apples on top of cabbage leaves and you'll have dessert.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar and syrup until peanuts split apart, boiling hard for about 20
minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir until soda is mixed.
Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, break up into pieces.

title: syrupy pork chops
directions: Mix Coke and sugar.
Place chops in baking dish, greased. Pour mixture over chops. Bake until done in 375° oven.

title: english butter toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Arrange saltines right side up in a single layer on bottom of pan. Melt butter and sugar in a medium size pan over medium heat. Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over crackers; spread evenly with spatula.
Bake 5 minutes (if crackers shift, rearrange with a fork).
Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes or just until top is set. Sprinkle with chocolate.
Let stand about 5 minutes until chocolate becomes shiny and soft, then spread evenly over top. Cool completely.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Place a pecan half on each piece.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Place opened
can of milk in freezer until crystallized (about 30 minutes).
Add
cup of boiling water to jello and put in the refrigerator
for	30 minutes.
Add lemon juice to frozen milk and
whip
for
5 minutes.	Combine jello and milk and whip again. Add nuts, apple and celery.
Put in mold.

title: pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.

title: baked fish a la debra
directions: Mix Stove Top as instructed on box.
Place canned fish and mushrooms in stuffing.
Mix thoroughly.
Melt butter.
Take 1/2 butter and pour in dish.
Put fish, stuffing and then fish on top. Pour remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add soda, salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon to sifted flour. Put all in large bowl and beat thoroughly until well blended. Grease and flour 3 tins, 2 large and 1 small or 3 large (3 large won't get quite so high and takes less baking time).
I usually use 4 small tins.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, until tester comes out clean.

title: twin mountain muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk, stirring only enough to mix.
Fill well-greased muffin tins to 1/2 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: orange scallops
directions: Combine zest, juice, oil and scallops in plastic bag. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Broil scallops 4 inches from heat for 6 minutes, until opaque.
Add parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, melted shortening and salt.
Pour over boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in milk and egg. Combine and add baking powder and corn meal.
Bake at 450°.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine the remaining ingredients with the ground beef.
Cook at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling, salted water 5 to 8 minutes or until just tender; drain.
Combine ground beef, egg, onion, rice, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Fold ends over and roll up. Place cabbage rolls, seam side down, in a large, greased skillet. Sprinkle cheese over cabbage rolls.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 1 cup of juice.
Arrange tomatoes on top of cabbage rolls.
Pour reserved tomato juice over rolls.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Simmer all ingredients except shrimp and cornstarch, about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer another 10 minutes.
Add enough water to cornstarch to mix well.
Pour into cooked mixture and mix. Serve over cooked rice.

title: chocolate chip sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir together flour and baking soda. In a mixing bowl, beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Beat in sour cream alternately with flour mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool, remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes one 10-inch cake.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add coloring, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour and cocoa together 3 times.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
In a cup mix soda and vinegar together, then fold into cake mixture.
Do not beat.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and do not flour.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Ice with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: delicious sauerkraut dish
directions: Brown ground meat in bacon grease.
Put all ingredients in roaster pan together.
Bake in oven at 300° about 2 hours.
Stir once or twice.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Bring broth, carrots and broccoli to a boil in saucepan. Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Saute onion in margarine until done (not brown).
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick.
Add broth, carrots and broccoli; heat mixture.
Add cheese; heat thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, butter, onion and mushrooms until broccoli has thawed.
Make sauce of soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Mix all ingredients, put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot creamy beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Stir in finely chopped beef, onion and seasonings.
Put into shallow baking dish.
Top with nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: paste
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water slowly, stirring constantly over low heat.
Remove when paste starts to thicken. It will thicken more as it cools.
Keep in covered jars.
Thin with water if necessary.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt in saucepan.
Blend in flour and salt until smooth.
Stir in cold milk.
Gradually add.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly until thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, if desired.

title: pink champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts.
Add other ingredients to the cream cheese mixture.
Freeze.
Thaw 1/2 hour before serving.
Keeps weeks in freezer.
Serves 8 to 10.
Use loaf pan. Return to freezer after slicing off what is needed.

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Combine hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast and warm water.
Add to first mixture. Then add 1 egg and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Store in refrigerator.
Punch down dough when double.
Divide and bake as needed.

title: pie crust
directions: Crumb all ingredients together.
Add 1 cup warm water.
Slowly mix with fork until well mixed.
Divide into 5 parts.
Knead each part lightly on a floured board and roll.
Makes five 9-inch pie shells that can be placed in the freezer and used at a later time.

title: arabian chicken
directions: Place chicken breast fillets on cutting board and pound with meat mallet until slightly flat.
Saute spinach in saucepan with butter (2 minutes).
Spread small portions of spinach on fillets with Feta cheese.
Holding mixture in center of the fillet, fold both sides and pin with a toothpick.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: curly lingemann's gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses, mixing well. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add a little at a time to creamed ingredients; mix well.
Take heaping teaspoonfuls and roll into balls, rolling each ball in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza dip spread
directions: Spread cream cheese and top with cocktail sauce.
Cover with onion, green pepper, tomatoes and black olives.
Top with cheese. Serve with crackers.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: peach cobbler(substitute any kind of fruit)
directions: Put sliced peaches in deep dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over peaches.
Place in 350° oven until golden brown.
Brush with butter.
Serve hot or cold.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix
the
ingredients together in a bowl, gently.
Pour into an
x 8-inch, lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: rigatoni and sausage
directions: Remove sausage meat from casings and brown in ovenproof Dutch oven.
Break
up
sausage with wooden spoon.
Drain off all
but 1
tablespoon
drippings.
Add peppers and onion and cook
until onion
is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Empty vegetables, juice and all, into pot.
Add cooked, cut-up chicken.
Add onions and seasonings.
Heat and eat.

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Wash and dry okra.
Chop into thin round slices.
Select a thick pot and put in enough oil to cover the bottom.
When the oil is hot, reduce fire to medium.
Add okra.
Cover to cook.
Remove cover often and stir to keep from sticking.
When stick substance has disappeared and okra is brownish, add onions, bell pepper, garlic and seasonings.
Permit onion and bell pepper to wilt a little, then add water and the tomato sauce.
Add chicken.
Cover and continue cooking for about 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook onion and celery in 3 cups broth.
Add rice, bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper, onion and pimento.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, cocoa, melted margarine and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time, until well mixed. Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture and mix well. Chill in freezer for several hours.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough in bowl of powdered sugar. Roll and shape into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: corn surprise
directions: Drain corn, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
In saucepan or skillet heat all ingredients until cream cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In medium saucepan, mix cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and taco seasoning; bring to a boil. Layer chips and chicken in a casserole dish. Pour soup mixture over the top of the chips and chicken. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: mini chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 24 muffin cups with foil or paper. Place one vanilla wafer in each cup.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in mini morsels.
Spoon 1/4 cup into each prepared muffin cup.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Rinse and drain chicken. Dip chicken in beaten eggs. Place crushed croutons and Parmesan cheese in large bowl or freezer bag. Mix well. Roll or shake the pieces of chicken in croutons and place on baking pan. Bake in oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients on low to medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add the mustard.
Stir well.
If too sour add a little milk.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in flour mixture and add vinegar, vanilla and oil.
Beat and add water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage very fine.
Put in skillet with melted bacon fat. Add salt and water; cook until cabbage is done. Add black pepper.

title: no cook pie
directions: Chill 9-inch pie pan 10 minutes.
Line pan with 1 pint vanilla ice cream, sides also.
Freeze.
Put softened strawberry on top of the vanilla; freeze.
Put last pint of vanilla on top; freeze. When serving, put whipped whip topping and nuts on top of pie.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil over high heat in large nonstick skillet.
Add chicken, onions and garlic to skillet.
Stir-fry 2 minutes. Reduce heat.
Stir in broth, beans, broccoli, mushrooms and ginger.
Simmer, covered, 6 to 8 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Mix together cornstarch and soy sauce; stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until sauce simmers and clears.
Makes 6 servings. Quick and delicious.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 to 10 minutes. Cook rice. Saute celery and onions. Mix together celery, onions, broccoli, rice and soup in baking dish. Swirl in Cheese Whiz. Sprinkle with paprika if desired. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: bologna cheese bake
directions: Combine potatoes, bologna, green pepper, onion and soup in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave 20 minutes on High or until potatoes are tender.
Top with grated cheese.
Let stand, uncovered, until cheese begins to melt.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, water, corn syrup, salt and butter in saucepan. Cook syrup to hard boil stage, when dropped in cold water.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and form into balls.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Prepare graham crackers as directed on box.
Press in bottom of paper cups.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Cream together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: In large roast pan or aluminum foil, place salted roast.
Add soup and onion.
Mix by pouring over roast.
Cover meat and bake according to the size of the roast.

title: green onion casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Season with salt and pepper. Place in greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook ground beef; brown onions in large skillet until meat loses color and onion is tender.
Drain excess fat.
Add other ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese, spinach or broccoli and scallions on top of unbaked pie shell.
Combine eggs, Ricotta cheese, milk, cornstarch, Italian seasonings, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat well and pour over cheese mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: butter brickle torte
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Beat ice cream into pudding mixture and freeze.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in oil until lightly browned.
Chop onion, green pepper and celery; add to rice and saute over low heat 5 minutes until tender.
Add tomatoes and pork and cook over low heat about 5 minutes.
Can also use beef, Spam or hamburg.
Serves 6.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix beans with dry taco seasoning, then layer: lettuce, beans, sour cream, salsa, cheese, olives and tomato.
Garnish with chips.

title: respectable chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, blending until sugar no longer crunches against bowl.
In separate bowl combine flours, soda and salt.
Add to a large bowl and blend thoroughly.
Add desired amount of chocolate chips. Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet (grease first time only).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Yields approximately 4 1/2 dozen decent sized cookies.
Warning: May be habit forming.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Add bananas; mix.
Add Bisquick and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan for about 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir flour and spices together.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs in bowl and beat until blended well.
Add the pumpkin; blend.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.

title: carrot cake(a family favorite for years)
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add oil and stir until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add carrots and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into three 9-inch greased pans.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Chill.
Serve as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in applesauce.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon into 36 greased tea-size (about 1 3/4-inch diameter) muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 425° oven about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
While muffins are warm, dip tops and sides into melted butter and then cinnamon sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream eggs, margarine and sugars. Blend in dry ingredients.
Add oats and chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: plum-barbecued chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove excess fat from chicken.
Place chicken, meaty sides up, in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Place remaining ingredients into work bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade or into blender container.
Cover and blend on medium speed until well blended.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 30 minutes; spoon pan juices over chicken.
Bake uncovered until thickest pieces are done, about 20 minutes longer.
Remove chicken to platter.
Stir pan juices; spoon over chicken.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet stewed tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in large skillet and stir well.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in a meat loaf pan.
Bake until done; spread small amount of ketchup on top.

title: homemade white bread
directions: In a 4-quart mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let mixture stand for 5 minutes, then add 1 1/2 cups warm water and 3 cups all-purpose flour.
Beat until smooth, about 100 strokes.
Cover; let rise 2 hours.

title: williamsburg chocolate pie
directions: Melt
margarine
and chocolate together.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add milk,
vanilla, chocolate and margarine. Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions.
Cover, cook and drain. Have cheese at room temperature.
Add butter and cheese to hot broccoli.
Stir until melted.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sausage ring 2(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly with fork.
Place in lightly greased 6 cup ring mold, then turn out onto foil lined shallow baking pan.
(Do not cook in mold.)
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Drain grease if necessary during baking.
Fill center with scrambled eggs or hash brown potatoes.
Garnish.

title: slush punch
directions: In a 6 quart container, combine sugar and gelatin powder.
Add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice; mix. Pour into plastic containers and freeze at least 24 hours.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix required amount of hot water with jello and let sit to cool.
Mix in pie filling and required amount of cold water (per jello mix).
Refrigerate to set.

title: spiced pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix flour, spice, baking powder, soda and salt in medium bowl. Mix pumpkin, sugar, juice, eggs, oil and extract in large bowl; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture and 3/4 cup nuts until moistened. Spoon into two (9 x 5-inch) greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle remaining nuts over top of loaves.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: copper penny carrot salad
directions: Mix and let stand.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 3 hours.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of batter in pan.
Spread 1 can of cherry pie filling on; cover with remaining batter. Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick spiced peaches
directions: Combine ingredients; heat to boiling.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Drain before serving.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper to make a dressing.

title: seafoam nut squares
directions: Mix flour,
salt, baking powder and soda.
Cream shortening, sugar, 1/2	cup
brown
sugar,
water and vanilla.	Add milk and mix
together with dry ingredients.
Spread into a 15 x 10-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, chunky fruit and mandarin oranges.
Mix and refrigerate. Mix remaining ingredients, except strawberries, together.
Add strawberries (frozen) just before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain and set aside.
Cover bottom of large dish with Tater Tots.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over Tater Tots.
Add hamburger meat over the soup.
Pour Cheddar cheese soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sylvia's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 3-inch deep dish glass or pan. Cook at 350° until it browns.
Serve warm.

title: company coleslaw
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients, except vegetables.
Let it cool, then pour over vegetables and chill well before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cut shortening in flour and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Mix slightly.
Add blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, then lower to simmer and stir occasionally for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until clear, on medium heat.
Add food coloring and nuts and boil to hard ball stage.
Take from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until dull.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch square pan, with fork, mash cream cheese until very soft.
Add sugar, flour and salt. Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients except pie filling.
Mix briskly with fork until thoroughly blended. Scrape sides of pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.
Spread with pie filling and chill. Serves 9.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until meat is ready to fall off bone.
Remove meat from stock (discard skin and bones) and cut into small pieces.
Return to 1-quart stock.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cool until potatoes are done.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: chili 101
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic until it crumbles and no longer pink. Drain. Add tomato sauce, seasonings and water. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer. Stir occasionally. Cook 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: In a glass casserole dish, put rice, water and melted butter. Put chicken breast in dish.
Spoon cream of chicken soup on top and in between chicken breasts.
Cover and bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the margarine and sugar. Beat in the egg and mashed bananas. Stir in the oatmeal and walnuts. Gradually add the flour, baking soda and salt mixture; mix well. Drop heaping teaspoonfuls of dough on an ungreased cookie sheet about 3-inches apart. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and add butter and sugar.
Beat well.
Add sifted flour and baking powder to mixture.
Beat egg whites until frothy; stir in.
Roll fruit in extra flour and add to mixture. Pour in tube pan to 1/2-inch of top.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat yolks, sugar and nutmeg about 10 minutes.
Gradually beat in liqueur.
Cover; chill.
Just before serving time, place mixture in a large punch bowl.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks, then cream.
Fold each gently into yolk mixture. Sprinkle with grated nutmeg.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well and split into 2 logs.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and seal tightly with foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Place butter in microwave-safe bowl, breaking it up into pieces. Microwave at High power for about 45 seconds. Cover with wax paper to prevent spattering. Beat in the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs. Combine flour, bran, oats and baking soda. Stir into butter mixture. Press out half of dough into an 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish. Shield corners of dish with foil to prevent overcooking. Microwave at High power for 4 to 5 minutes, turning a quarter turn 3 times during baking. Cool before cutting into bars.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and egg yolks.
Add vanilla and salt and blend.
Set aside.
Put raisins in hot water in a saucepan and heat until raisins become puffy.
Strain.
Combine raisins to other mixed ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Combine with other ingredients and boil for 30 minutes.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: hockey pucks
directions: Spread a generous amount of peanut butter and sandwich between 2 Ritz crackers.
Repeat until box of crackers is finished.
Melt the chocolate almond bark over low heat (approximately 8 to 10 minutes).
If chocolate becomes too thick, add 1 tablespoon Crisco shortening until melted.
Dip crackers into melted chocolate with fork; hold over pan until excess chocolate drips off.
Place on aluminum foil to dry.
Repeat until all cookies are gone.
These are a very easy cookie to make and they freeze wonderfully.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix everything well; put in a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs; dot with butter and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 5.

title: german oat cake
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool about 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup coconut and 1 cup pecans.
Spread on cake.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients and mix with spoon and pour into buttered square pan.
When cool, cut into squares and refrigerate. Makes about 5 pounds.

title: funnel cake
directions: Add all fruit.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs and oil; blend well.
Add pecans and fruit, mixing well.
Pour into 3 tube or Bundt pans.
Cakes can also be made in 9-inch single pans, well greased and floured.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients until absorbed.

title: myra's lefsa
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Rice when cool.
Add other ingredients, starting with 2 1/2 cups flour but never more than 3 to 3 1/2 cups.
Roll and bake.

title: texas slab cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix flour and sugar; set aside. In a pan, bring to boil the oleo, cocoa and water. Pour over flour. Add buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon, soda, salt and vanilla. Pour into a greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 minutes. Prepare Frosting the last 3 minutes.

title: cream cheese pineapple cake
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press mixture into pan.
Add pineapple (drained) over cake mix.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar well.
Pour over pineapple and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spicy pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out dough on floured board.
Spread tomato paste thinly all over dough.
Add cheese and pepperoni.
Roll dough up and tuck in ends.
Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet until golden brown, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from oven and brush with melted butter.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain.
In a heavy frying pan, heat 1/4 cup peanut oil.
Saute sliced onions until transparent.
Add sliced tomatoes and saute, then add tomato paste, thyme and cayenne pepper.
Mix well.
Add chicken and simmer until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: fettuccine with spinach and feta cheese
directions: Wash spinach until no trace of sand remains.
Drain spinach in colander and set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, add onion, Feta cheese, oil, lemon juice, dill and pepper.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions, but without salt.
For last 30 seconds of cooking, stir spinach into fettuccine and push it under boiling water to wilt.
Drain pasta and spinach; add to cheese mixture.
Toss.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients;
pour into pretty glass bowl.

title: onion and cheese chicken bake(microwave)
directions: Melt butter in glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add seasoned salt.
Roll chicken in seasoned butter to coat.
Arrange in dish.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: ice cream jello delight
directions: Dissolve lime and lemon jello, sugar and boiling water in large bowl.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin with 1/2 cup water in small bowl.
Combine and stir.
Add softened ice cream and peach slices.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: crab puffs
directions: Beat together water, butter and salt; add 1/2 cup flour, stirring constantly until mixture is thick.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Keep mixture over heat until thickened (at this point stir vigorously to prevent burning). Remove from heat.
Add parsley, Worcestershire sauce, onion and Old Bay and mix well.
Gently fold in crabmeat.
Chill mixture 15 to 20 minutes.
Using a teaspoon lift up a small amount of mixture.
With the hand roll the mixture into a small ball about 1 inch in diameter.
Drop into very hot oil and cook until lightly browned. Drain on absorbent paper.
Use immediately or freeze for later use. To reheat, place in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: approximately 50.

title: hobo beans
directions: Fry hamburger with onion; add bacon.
Mix in beans.
Add remaining ingredients together and mix in with hamburger and beans. This recipe cooks good in a roaster pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Cook as directed. Cool.

title: chicken rice skillet
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown well in butter in skillet.
Add water and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Push to one side of skillet or keep warm on serving platter.
Stir remaining ingredients into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza
directions: In a large bowl place yeast, water water, egg, oil and sugar. Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Stir until dough forms a ball and is smooth and elastic.
Then knead it.
Place in bowl and let rest 5 minutes.
Spread dough on a lightly greased pizza tray.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes.
Spread pizza or spaghetti sauce evenly over pizza crust.
Put whatever toppings you want on it.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: delicious lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Slowly stir at least half the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue. Bake.
Serve as soon as cool.

title: lentil supper *
directions: Saute onions, celery, carrots and garlic.
Add lentils and vegetable broth to sauteed vegetables.
Cover and cook for approximately 45 minutes.
Cook orzo separately in vegetable broth.
Add to lentil mixture before serving.
A good one dish meal, enhanced with a salad and bread.
Serve in a bowl.
